title: lemon velvet cake
directions: Mix lemon jello and hot water and let cool, but not set.
Put lemon cake mix in large bowl; add oil and eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Add lemon jello; mix and bake at 350° in a 10 x 16-inch greased and floured pan.
Glaze immediately from oven with powdered sugar with lemon juice.
Punch holes in cake with toothpicks and pour glaze over cake.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple, but save the juice (1/4 cup). Mix and form into balls the ground beef and bread crumbs. Brown meatballs in skillet.
Drain fat.
Mix together the ketchup, brown sugar, pineapple juice, soy sauce and lemon juice. Add this mixture to meatballs in skillet. Add the drained pineapple chunks.
Heat to warm.
Best if made in the morning and allowed to stand in sauce. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add the milk, butter, corn, sugar and seasonings to eggs. Turn into a greased casserole and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until the pudding is set.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: grandma ruby's cheese biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients; let rise in a warm place for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pat out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into 2-inch rounds. Place on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gilda's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla, water and eggs, then add flour, baking soda, salt and milk chocolate chips.
Bake at 375°.
This is a double batch.

title: easy lemonade
directions: Mix lemons, sugar and boiling water and allow to cool before pouring over ice cubes.
Delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add zucchini; then add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into a large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done (about one hour).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend chicken, celery, soup, onion, pimentos and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: party pizzas
directions: Combine first four
ingredients
in
a	bowl; mix well. Spread on party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
In a saucepan, bring to boil butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla in another bowl, then add to above mixture and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured shallowed cake pan, approximately 20 minutes at 350°, then immediately pour frosting over cake when removed from oven.

title: pork chops a la gretchen
directions: Place layer of potatoes in casserole. top with onions, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add pork chops, pour milk over and sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350.

title: russian rock cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: baked carrots and apples
directions: Pare the carrots and cut.
Cook carrots in salted water until tender and crisp; drain.
Place in a 10-inch glass pie plate or long, square casserole dish.
Put apples, just as they come from the can, over the carrots and mix together.
Sprinkle sugar over all and dot with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good with all baked meats.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds, together.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This recipe freezes beautifully.

title: caramel-nut brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup of milk and mix well. Press 1/2 of mixture in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Mash the eggs to a paste with a fork, then mix with the butter, lemon rind and flour.
Bring the milk to a boil in a saucepan, then add gradually, stirring constantly, to the paste. Return to saucepan.
Add the crabmeat and simmer for 3 minutes. stirring constantly.
Add the cream and sherry and bring to a boil.
Season with pepper and serve.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Put sliced potatoes on bottom of greased casserole.
Salt and pepper.
Layer of sliced carrots, salt and pepper.
Layer of cabbage, chopped fine, salt and pepper.
Add butter.
Little celery, pour can of tomatoes.
Add pork chops.
Bake 3/4 hour or until pork chops are done.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain. Arrange in 8-inch square pan. In saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring occasionally.
Blend in cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake uncovered 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Garnish with tomato slices and bake 5 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In heavy 2-quart pan, stir together syrup, sugar, water, salt, butter and vinegar.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until temperature reaches 270° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Slowly pour over popcorn, stirring to coat well.
When just cool enough, but warm, shape into balls.
Keep in plastic wrap.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until thoroughly creamed. Combine Cool Whip with creamed mixture.
Mix butter with crumbs. Press crumbs in square dish, reserving part for layers.
Next add a layer of cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pie filling for next layer.
Add remaining part of cream cheese and Cool Whip; top with crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: lou's cucumber pickles(makes 3 pints)
directions: It's so easy.
You just mix the whole thing in a big bowl. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Transfer it to jars with lids and refrigerate for 3 days.
This makes the best tasting pickles you ever tasted.

title: teriyaki ginger sauce
directions: This sauce is great for boneless, skinless chicken breasts or chicken kabobs.

title: scripture cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10
x
14-inch
angel cake tube pan. Preheat oven to slow (325°).

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Put pie filling and pineapple in bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on next.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Wash and stem berries.
Crush berries into small bits either with potato masher or in food processor.
Measure out 2 cups of the berries and put into large bowl.
Measure sugar into a separate bowl (make sure measurements are level).
Stir sugar into fruit.
Set aside for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then mix 3/4 cup water and the box of Sure-Jell fruit pectin in small saucepan (it may be lumpy before cooking).
Bring mixture to boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring for 1 minute.
Stir hot Sure-Jell fruit pectin mixture into fruit mixture.
Stir constantly for 3 minutes.
(A few sugar crystals may remain.)
Fill clean containers to within 1/2 inch of top.
Wipe off top edges of containers; quickly cover with lids. Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours, then place in freezer. After opening, store in refrigerator.
This is a delicious jam, almost like fresh berries.
Good on ice cream, too.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soups (do not dilute). Mix in large bowl.
Add rice, broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Stir well. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Blend all together in large mixing bowl, adding chicken breasts last.
Add enough broth from boiled chicken breasts to have thick consistency.
Bake at 375° until center is firm.
Serve with chicken broth, 2 diced boiled eggs, 1 can celery soup and 1/2 cup of uncooked dressing mix.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix together and serve as gravy.
Chopped chicken livers may be used, if desired.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides; salt and pepper to taste. Drain sauerkraut and rinse slightly, if desired.
Lay pork chops in baking pan.
Add sauerkraut on top of pork chops.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until nice and browned on top.
While baking cover with foil the first 40 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
In large bowl, combine meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, oil and corn.
Pour half the batter into greased iron skillet dusted with meal.
Add meat and top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients. Cut in peanut butter. Add oatmeal, egg and milk. Stir only until blended.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Cool.
Serve with jelly.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Mix altogether.
Drop from teaspoon onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° (about 15 minutes per tray).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Add water gradually.
Add oil and pumpkin.
Mix flour and seasonings and mash with first mixture. Mix ingredients together.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat lightly.
Add onion and grated Longhorn cheese.
Place 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in each tortilla and roll.
Place, side by side, in baking dish.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease pan.
Measure first 7 ingredients into a large bowl. In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in zucchini and oil. Stir all at once into flour.
Mix just until moist.
Spoon into pans.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean in 400° oven.
Remove and cool on racks or serve warm.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and eggs (one at a time, beating after each).
Add sour cream and vanilla, then beat.
Mix 3 tablespoons light brown sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Grease pan.
Put half the cake mixture in the pan and sprinkle half the sugar mixture on the cake.
Then pour the remaining cake mixture and top with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix vegetables.
Combine yogurt, mustard and sugar; toss with vegetables.
Cover and chill at least one hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening.
Add yeast dissolved in small amount of warm water.
Add buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Roll out and cut into biscuits as needed.
Bake at 450°.
Dough will keep several days.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Line dish with enough foil to wrap over top of dish.
Layer potatoes and onions, then salt and pepper.	Cut margarine over top and wrap.
About 10 minutes before done, uncover and brown.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flavorings.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well, then pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 15 people.

title: grandma's pineapple jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Drain pineapple and save juices.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O. Chill until partially thickened.
Soften cream cheese and beat with mayonnaise.
Add to Jell-O and stir well.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in mold and chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: holiday squares
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo, then add eggs, one at a time. Mix in rest of ingredients, except pie filling, and beat until smooth.
Grease jelly roll pan 15 x 10 x 1-inch.
Pour in mixture.
Before baking, cut into 2 inch squares.
Make indention in the center of each square with a teaspoon.
Put a teaspoon of cherry pie filling into each square.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Cool, then cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: acorn squash with fruit
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place in 12-inch plate, hollow side down and stems to the outside.
Cover with plastic and microwave on High for 10 minutes, turning plate after 5 minutes.
Test to see if done.
Do not pierce skin.
Let stand while preparing fruit.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch and the 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Blend well.
Stir in fruit. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in butter.
Lightly salt each squash and fill with fruit.
Serves 4.

title: shells and shellfish salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Mix Ranch dressing, lemon juice and pepper after pasta has been drained and chilled with cold water.
Add dressing mixture and stir lightly.
Add seafood last.
Season to taste.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: venison or beef roast
directions: Roast meat in 350° oven until done.
Shred meat, removing bones, gristle and fat.
Stir together onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Stir meat and soup mixture together and place in a slow cooker.
Cook on low for 3 - 4 hours or more.
Serve with wild rice.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, baking powder, eggs, vanilla, salt and oil; mix well.
Stir in zucchini and raisins.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°, until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
When cool, cake may be cut in bars and frozen.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain the beets, saving 1/4 cup of the liquid.
In a 1-quart saucepan, stir together the cornstarch and sugar.
Gradually stir in the beet juice and vinegar, keeping smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add the beets and heat gently.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add water.
Thicken with flour.
Add remainder of ingredients and simmer.
Watch closely.
Burns easily!
Serve on warmed hamburger rolls.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs and mix together. Add water (or fruit juice) and honey, mixing well. In small bowl, sift together the 2 cups flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and baking soda. Add to the batter and mix well. Mix the 1 cup of sifted flour with the fancy diced mixed fruit and nuts and add to the batter. Line 2 greased 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch loaf pans with waxed paper, allowing 1/2-inch to extend above all sides of pan. Pour batter into pans. Do not flatten. Bake in preheated 275° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Place pan containing 2 cups water on bottom shelf while baking. Cakes baked with water in oven have greater volume, moist texture and a smooth, shiny glaze. If decoration of nuts and cherries are used, place on cake at end of 2 hours. Store in a covered container in a cool place. This recipe makes about 4 1/2 pounds.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 3 items.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients plus nuts and dates and add together.
Add milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 13 minutes or more.

title: french chocolate(very fancy)
directions: In saucepan combine chocolate pieces, syrup and water.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted. Stir in vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until cool.
In large mixer bowl, beat whipping cream on medium speed, gradually adding the cooled chocolate syrup.
Continue beating until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Turn into bowl; chill.
Just before serving, heat milk to scalding.
Pour milk into heated coffeepot or carafe.
Fill serving cups half full of chocolate whipped cream.
Pour in hot milk; mix gently.
Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Heat in larger pan.
Cream the milk, sugar and butter; bring to soft boil. Boil for 12 minutes (boil easy).
Mix in rest; heat until melted completely.
Turn into greased container.
Cool; cut into pieces. Makes 5 pounds.

title: greek corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° until done.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix in order and pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes (until set).
Makes two (9-inch) pies or 18 tarts.

title: filipino fruit salad
directions: Drain all
ingredients	from cans and bottles.	Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: vishey squa
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Saute onions, leeks and celery. Stir until limp.
Stir in potatoes and stock; cook until potatoes are tender.
Puree in blender and chives; stir in cream. Refrigerate.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Blend in food blender or mixer until smooth.
(Like sour cream.)

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into very thin slices (1/8 to 1/4-inch thick). Place the slices in a colander, sprinkle with salt and let drain for 10 minutes.

Wash and wipe slices. Dip slices in flour, then in beaten eggs seasoned with salt and pepper. Fry slices in hot oil until lightly brown and turn over. Arrange slices in a casserole. Add layers of sauce, sliced Mozzarella cheese and grated cheese.
Repeat until all eggplant is used. To top layer, add more tomato sauce, Mozzarella cheese and grated cheese. Sprinkle with oregano and pepper. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare and layer in a casserole dish in order given. Refrigerate.

title: peach and yogurt parfait
directions: Peel and pit peaches, then cut into chunks.
In a medium bowl, combine peaches, brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Toss until well blended.
Let mixture stand until sugar dissolves and peaches become juicy, about 5 minutes.
Layer peaches and yogurt in parfait glasses.
Serve.
Serves 4. Each serving contains 178 calories.

title: sweet and sour mini onions
directions: Drain onions thoroughly on paper towels.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
When it foams, add drained onions.
Saute over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until onions begin to color. Mix brown sugar, vinegar and salt to form a smooth paste.
Add to onions and stir to coat onions.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Sauce should be thick and coat onions.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: *Other flavors may be used or one kind.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour or until chicken is cooked through.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in microwave-safe bowl.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat the oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Stir in the chili powder and pressed garlic.
Add the zucchini and bell pepper.
Saute the vegetables until they are tender-crisp, then stir in the cooked grain, optional tofu and kidney beans.
Stir the tomato sauce and oregano into the Ricotta or cottage cheese; pour this mixture into the frying pan.
Stir; top with grated cheese and cover.
Cook over low heat until the cheese is melted. Garnish and serve with warm tortillas.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Slice mushrooms, chop pepper, celery, carrots and squash. Separate cauliflower.
Combine first seven ingredients. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill 3 hours or more.
Serves 12.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well before serving.

title: oodles of noodles
directions: Melt butter in skillet and brown ground beef. Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Cook noodles and fold in cottage cheese, sour cream and onion.
Spoon half the mixture into bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with half of the meat mixture. Repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Can be refrigerated at this point.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add flour, oyster juice and milk to make a white sauce.

title: maple nut cake
directions: In a large bowl combine melted butter, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Blend with electric mixer on high speed until batter is well mixed.
Grease a tube pan with butter generously.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party snacks
directions: Mix oil and seasonings together.
Put crackers in a large bag. Pour oil and seasonings over crackers.
Shake well.
Store in an airtight container with paper towel in bottom overnight.

title: paprika egg dip
directions: Mash eggs and cream cheese together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in container and sprinkle paprika on top.

title: mom, mom jenny's cheese log
directions: Combine flour, butter and sour cream. Divide in 4 portions. Wrap each portion in wax paper and chill.
Roll individual balls on well floured surface. Roll each 12 x 6-inches.
Sprinkle dough with salt and pepper.
Cover dough with 3/4 cup cheese.
Start with 12-inch side and roll like jelly roll.
Place seam down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make cuts halfway through dough and approximately 1-inch apart.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 5-cup fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and chill in refrigerator for several hours (overnight is better) before serving.

title: red cabbage dish
directions: Saute onion, bay leaf and cabbage in bacon fat.
Add apples and moisten with red wine.
Continue to cook about 1 1/2 hours. Add sugar and jelly. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Delicious with ham.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large roaster or casserole dish. Cover.
Bake in 250° oven for about 5 hours.
Do not peek.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine in large bowl of the electric mixer until the consistency of heavy mayonnaise.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add brandy or fruit juice.
Sift together the dry ingredients and sprinkle over the fruits and nuts. Gradually add to the creamed mixture and beat until blended.
This mixture will be very crumbly.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pat in small greased tube pan.
Bake in a 250° preheated electric oven or roaster for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Yield:
About 3 1/4 pounds.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Split and butter muffins and place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toast under broiler until golden brown. Place 2 tablespoons Cheddar cheese on each muffin.
Cut frankfurters crosswise into 1/4-inch slices; arrange on muffins. Top each with 2 tablespoons pizza sauce; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven or until heated through.
Allow 2 mini pizzas per serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: coffee bubble ring
directions: Melt butter; scald milk. Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1/4 cup butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl. Sprinkle or crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Stir in remaining 2 cups flour.
Mix until well blended. Cover. Let rise in warm place, free from drafts, until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/2 of the evaporated milk in double boiler (keep warm).
Blend cake mix with the other 1/2 of the evaporated milk and melted butter.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Spread 1/2 of cake mixture in bottom of greased 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Spread caramels over cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spoon drop rest of cake mixture (mixed with 1/2 the nuts) over that. Sprinkle with the rest of the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups sugar, oil, molasses and eggs, beating well.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt into liquid mixture.
Mix well (very stiff dough).
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip and layer on cooled bottom crust.
Mix pistachio pudding and milk; layer on top of Cool Whip.
The rest of Cool Whip layered on pudding mixture and sprinkle with nuts.

title: fruitcake
directions: Combine dates, pecans, red and green cherries and pineapple in large bowl; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients; add to fruit mixture, stirring well.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased and brown paper lined 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake completely in pan; then remove from pan and remove brown paper.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a large pot filled with water, place chicken breasts, bouillon cubes and stick of margarine; bring to a boil.
Boil (on low) for approximately 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked. Remove chicken breasts, tear chicken off in strips and place back in pot.
Add frozen noodles and cook for additional half hour or so, until noodles are tender.
Stir occasionally so noodles separate.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: snack mix
directions: Break pretzels into bite-size pieces.
Mix with other ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil until soft, not browned. Add garlic powder and rice.
Heat thoroughly. Beat egg with fork.
Add to mixture with soy sauce.
Cook, stirring, until hot and the eggs are firm. Serves 4 to 6.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir flour mixture into shortening and sugar until no dry flour shows.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs, condensed milk and mince meat until well blended. Fold in flour and baking soda.
Add candied fruit, walnuts and pecans.
Spoon into Bundt pan or angel food pan.
You may fashion whole candied cherries and whole pecans in fluted edges of pan before putting batter in.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Makes a great center piece on any holiday table.

title: taco pie
directions: Set oven for 350°.
Put onion and ground chuck in a skillet and cook until well done.
Drain meat.
Add tomato sauce and beans. Heat.
Pour over half of the Doritos which have been crushed in a cake pan.
Top with remaining whole Doritos.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until hot.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix together the pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 7 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: mushroom tarts
directions: Clean and chop onions, parsley and mushrooms and heat in pan with the oil. Add butter. When hot, add vegetables, stirring constantly for 6 minutes. Add the rest. Fill tart shells. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden. A good make ahead appetizer.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Let raise until double in bulk.
Roll out and cut in size desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients until glaze consistency.
Pour over cake, then sprinkle top with toasted pecans.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook spaghetti. Saute onions, celery, pepper and mushrooms.
Melt cheese and tomatoes together.
Mix everything together.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Salt, if needed after mixing.

title: garlic cheese(snack on ritz)
directions: Mix cream cheese and cheese until well mixed.
Sprinkle garlic powder while mixing.
Add nuts and work into one large or two small balls.
Sprinkle wax paper with paprika or cayenne pepper according to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cheese and sausage need to be room temperature.

title: mary's chili
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes.
They will roll and brown by themselves.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: fudge bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat again.
Add melted butter and melted chocolate, vanilla and salt and beat again.
Add sifted flour and mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: kafta (oval-shaped meat balls)
directions: Put all of the above in a blender and grind until ingredients are completely mashed (all together).
Put the mixture in a bowl and start taking bunches and roll into oval shaped meat balls (hands should be wet when rolling into balls).
You can either fry in boiling oil or you can bake them in the oven.
Enjoy.

title: iced sugar cookies
directions: Prepare sugar cookies.
In clean mixer bowl, at high speed, beat egg white with lemon juice until frothy.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar.
Beat mixture about 5 minutes or until very thick and white.
Tint if desired with paste or liquid food coloring.
Pipe or spread about 1 teaspoon icing onto each baked and cooled cookie.
Let dry until hardened.
Add 50 calories (optional).

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in large, shallow microwave baking dish. Heat, uncovered, on Simmer for 14 minutes. Turn spareribs over and heat on Simmer for 14 minutes. Drain off excess fat.
Combine chili powder and barbecue sauce.
Pour half of the sauce over ribs. Heat, uncovered, on Simmer for 8 minutes.
Turn spareribs again. Sprinkle with lemon juice, if desired.
Pour on remaining sauce and heat, uncovered, on Simmer for 16 minutes or until fork-tender.
Pork should always be cooked until well done.

title: "ants on a log"
directions: Let children spread peanut butter on celery sticks and add raisins.
Nutritional and fun to do.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix flour and margarine well.
Then mix in other ingredients and make into balls.
Press with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, 1/3 cup water, salt and pepper. Shape into 22 (1-inch) meatballs.
Blend soup and chili powder, stir in water and bring to boil.
Add meatballs, cover and simmer gently 1 hour, stirring now and then.
Makes 7 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Stir in the sugar slowly.
Fold in nuts, chips, vanilla and salt.
Spoon onto aluminum foil covered cookie sheet.
Turn off oven.
Place cookies inside and forget!
Ready when cookies are hard enough to peel off foil.

title: vegetable cheese soup with popcorn
directions: Heat margarine in 3-quart nonstick saucepan, over low heat, until melted.
Stir in flour.
Cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth, carrot, celery and onion.
Heat to boiling and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are crisp-tender (about 8 minutes).
Stir in milk, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Stir constantly until hot and cheese has melted, 2 or 3 minutes longer (do not boil).
Top with popcorn. Makes 4 servings, about 1 cup soup and 1/4 cup popcorn.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Add syrup.
Mix well.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each egg. Mix together milk, vanilla and baking powder.
Add this to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Pour into greased and floured large tube pan.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open door for 1 hour. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend together the buttermilk, sugar and yeast mixture; stir into flour mixture and blend well. If necessary, add more buttermilk to make softer dough.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead 30 seconds.
Divide dough in half. Roll out 1/2 inch thick; cut out with cutter.
Bake immediately for biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together.
Put in a gallon jug and finish filling jug with water.
Freeze in a tray and chill the rest.
When ready to serve, pour in ginger ale.

title: easy hot wings
directions: Fry wings in oil until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper grocery bag.
Melt margarine and add hot sauce in pan.
Pour sauce over wings or dip into sauce.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream, sugar, lemon juice, almond and salt.
Add fruit. Fill muffin tins (lined with cupcake liners) and freeze.
When frozen, remove and put in plastic bags.
Take out 5 minutes before serving.
Paper will come off easily.
Serve on lettuce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease a 9-inch square casserole dish.
Combine eggs, flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt.
Mix together. Add butter.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and cook until golden brown.

title: salmon rice pie
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Break salmon in large chunks and distribute over bottom of Rice Crust.
Sprinkle broccoli over salmon.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in saucepan; boil 2 minutes. Stir in coconut.
Spoon over warm cake.

title: almond apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples; slice in 1/8-inch slices.
Dissolve sugar and water over medium heat.
Add apples, nutmeg and lemon rind. Cook slowly at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Pour filling into crust.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put apples in cake batter.
Roll nuts, fruit cake mix and raisins in flour before mixing in batter.
Makes 4 layers.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first eight ingredients. Pour mixture into large baking dish. Mix cornflakes and remaining margarine, spread on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Cut leaves from cabbage head; don't tear leaves.
Drop leaves into boiling water.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set oven at 375°.
Mix ingredients altogether as for meat loaf.
Divide mixture into 8 small loaves like.
Wrap in leaves.
Place in greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add zucchini and chopped onion. Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring often, until zucchini is soft but not browned.
Combine half of the zucchini mixture, 2 cups chicken broth, the curry (if used), salt and cayenne in food processor or blender.
Puree.
Pour into saucepan if serving hot or into large bowl if serving cold.
Repeat pureeing with remaining ingredients.
Combine batches.
If serving hot, heat soup in saucepan and garnish with croutons.
If serving cold, chill 2 hours.
Garnish with chives.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dodie's refrigerator slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, celery seed, mustard and salt in medium saucepan; bring to boil.
Alternate layers of cabbage and onions in a container with tight fitting lid.
Pour hot dressing over vegetables.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweeter muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients until moist.
Fill greased cups 2/3 full.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deviled ham and pineapple dip
directions: In a bowl, mix deviled ham with cream cheese.
Drain syrup from pineapple.
Add pineapple to cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: lean chinese chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine vinegar, sugar, oil, 1 tablespoon soy and chicken.
Add shredded lettuce, tomatoes, onions and cilantro; mix.
Mound salad equally onto leaves on 4 to 6 plates.
Add soy to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Whip the cream and add sugar and vanilla.

title: spicy garlic shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel shrimp.
In a mixing bowl, combine herbs, garlic, salt, pepper, shallots and shrimp.
Oil a cookie sheet with olive oil and place shrimp on pan.
Grill for 2 minutes or until pink on both sides.
Bake for 2 minutes until brown. Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together except flour.
Stir well, then add flour. Add nuts, if desired.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Double this for a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients. Cook in unbaked pie shell. Start at 375° for 15 minutes. Then reduce heat to 350° and cook for 30 minutes.

title: double onion dip
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: tennessee spirit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in freezer.
Just before it freezes, process in a blender.
Serve in stemmed glasses.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, and syrup in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over popcorn immediately and mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Place in large roaster and bake at 200 degrees for 1 hour.
Pour on waxed paper and separate grains.

title: date balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, dates and egg together.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring all the while.
Remove from heat and when cool add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in Angel Flake coconut.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Add nuts to slightly whipped egg white.
Stir until nuts are well coated.
If necessary, add 1/2 to 1 teaspoon water.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over nuts and mix.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Will stick a little.
Cool a minute.
Scrape off onto wax paper.

title: baked salmon with mustard and tarragon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place salmon, skin down, on ungreased roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Whisk mayonnaise, mustard, tarragon and vinegar in small bowl.
Season topping to taste with salt and pepper.
Spread topping over top and sides of salmon completely covering it.
Cover pan tightly with heavy foil. Bake salmon covered until almost cooked through (salmon will feel almost firm when pressed) about 35 minutes.
Remove from oven. Preheat broiler.
Uncover pan.
Broil until topping is deep golden brown.
Salmon feels firm, 5 minutes.
Cut salmon crosswise into 4 pieces.
Slide spatula between skin/salmon.
Transfer to plate. Add lemon wedges.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix the ingredients together and make into balls.
Put in baking dish.

title: stafford meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake.

title: quick pickled peaches
directions: Drain peaches; to syrup from peaches, add sugar, vinegar and spices and boil 5 minutes. Add peaches and simmer 5 minutes. Allow fruit to stand in pickling syrup overnight. Serve chilled.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas under running cold water to separate; drain.
Heat peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper just to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; keep warm while preparing biscuits.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook hamburger in water until done.
Drain water.
For smooth sauce with no chunks, run through a food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil all peppers, vinegar, sugar and salt at a rapid boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add Certo.
Stir until partially cool; the mixture will be smooth.
Ladle into hot jars and seal. Works well with paraffin seals.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°. Spread apple filling in buttered 9-inch square
baking
dish or pan.

title: hummus
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pine nuts and parsley, in food processor.
Serve as a dip for raw vegetables or pita bread. Garnish with parsley and toasted pine nuts.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: marie's broccoli soup
directions: Cook all except last 3 ingredients until done.
Add milk.
Use a little of the milk with flour or cornstarch.
Add cheese.

title: "pain in the neck" chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9-inch pans. Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar until blended. Add eggs; beat until smooth. Stir in zucchini and vanilla. Alternately stir in nuts, dry ingredients and milk. Add chocolate chips.
Pour into pans and bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix all the ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°).

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli.
In saucepan, mix remaining ingredients together and simmer.
Drain broccoli and stir into mixture. Place in a casserole dish.

title: custard sauce
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks, salt and sugar. Gradually stir in scalded milk. Cook in double boiler over hot water until mixture coats spoon, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Chill 2 1/2 hours.

title: jerrie's russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in jars.
Add 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: toll-or-eens
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, add tomato soup, mushroom soup, water, noodles and cook until tender and add corn and olives. Bake in casserole dish 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Let stand 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice and cook potatoes and onion in salt water.
When potatoes and onion are done, drain and mash.
Add milk, butter and pepper. Bring to a boil and serve.

title: pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Mix all of these ingredients.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell, unbaked.
Cook 5 minutes at 350° and 40 minutes at 300°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix egg and sugar together and beat.
Sift flour and salt together.
Make a hole in flour and add shortening.
Add sugar and egg.
Add 2 cups water.
Mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Put in refrigerator; cover with wet towel.
Use as needed (will keep three days).
Roll out and let rise to double in size.
Bake at 400°.

title: fish cake roll
directions: Slice meats, bamboo shoots, round onion and celery in strips. Mix fish cake well with egg, cornstarch and seasonings.
Add chopped and sliced ingredients to fish cake mixture and mix well. (Add chopped black mushrooms and chopped fresh water chestnuts, if desired.)
Then put mixture onto all-purpose spring roll wrappers (available at your supermarket's refrigerated section or buy lumpia wrappers).
Wrap and roll.
Heat 1 quart oil in pot for deep frying.
Place rolls in hot oil.
Fry to golden brown.
Slice when cool to desired length.

title: super salmon bake
directions: Bring water to boil in bottom of double boiler.
In top of boiler, put milk, bread and butter.
Then heat until creamy.
Beat eggs; add the salmon, salt, pepper and onion.
Add hot milk mixture; stir well.
Put in greased baking dish; bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: layered chocolate elegance
directions: Bake brownie mix as per package instructions; cool and crumble in bite size pieces.
Divide in half.
Mix mousse according to package directions; omit cooling.
Crumble candy bars and divide in half.
Use a straight sided crystal bowl.
Sprinkle each pile of brownie crumbs with liqueur.
Put 1/2 in bowl; add 1/2 of mousse mixture in smooth layer.
Next add 1/2 candy bars in nice layer, then layer 1/3 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble the beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole, then stir in onion.
Micro-cook, covered, on 100% power (High) 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until done.
Drain, then stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder.
Micro-cook, covered, on High about 6 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spritz cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in raw egg.
Gradually blend in flour.
Fill cookie press.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all juice and use enough juice to make 2 cups. Mix juice with pudding mix and beat with mixer until thick. Fold in fruit and mix well. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: In medium saucepan, combine gelatin and 2 cups light cream. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a slight boil.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into eggs.
Return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the remaining cream and the vanilla.
In large bowl, combine cocoa powder and Equal gradually blending in egg mixture until smooth. Chill just until cold, stirring occasionally.
(Don't overchill.) Freeze in a 4-quart ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes about 1 3/4 quarts (14 half-cup servings). Contains 128 calories.
Food Exchange:
1/2 Milk, 1 1/2 Fat.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Chop chicken very fine.
Mix onion, parsley, oregano, celery and egg with chicken.
Place lasagna noodles on bottom of casserole dish; top with chicken mixture.
Pour tomatoes over; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until cheese is well melted.

title: breakfast in an orange(servings:  4)
directions: One of each ingredient per person.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix together.
Spread in glass pie pan.
Spread salsa over pie.
Add shredded lettuce, tomato, pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie shell.
Beat eggs lightly with rotary beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
(Place on cookie sheet to prevent spills.)
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with whip cream, if desired.

title: slushy punch
directions: Cook sugar and water to boil; set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with first mixture.
Freeze.

title: 4-layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter and add flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 375° or 30 minutes at 325°. Let cool completely.

title: muffins
directions: Grease muffin tin lightly with oil.
Sift flour together with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Stir quickly, only until barely blended.
Do not beat.
Fill each tin to 2/3 full of batter.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield: 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.
Contains 175 calories.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown onions, garlic and green pepper in butter and then add all the squash in the pan for about 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and stir in grated cheese.
Put into a casserole dish and sprinkle the
top
with a thin layer of bread crumbs.
Put into oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice.
Add all other ingredients and toss lightly.
I grind all my ingredients in the food processor.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and cook in skillet.
Break tortillas into small pieces and put into bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh blackberry cake
directions: Cook blackberries and mash up.
Cream butter and sugar with mixer.
Add other ingredients and mix by hand.
Add berries and alternate with flour that has been sifted with all spices and soda.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating slightly.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can use cream frosting or sour cream icing.

title: sourdough pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: choco-cherry nut drops
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add brown and white sugar, creaming well.
Blend in egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients gradually, blending well. Stir in chips, nuts and cherries.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: emma's meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, ground turkey, sausage, garlic powder, chili powder and oregano.
Press mixture into baking pan and bake on 450° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain excess juices, saving 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix 1/4 cup juice from meat loaf with sweet leaf basil, tomato sauce and diced tomatoes.
Pour topping over meat loaf and bake for 15 minutes.

title: hot mushroom cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread bread pan with vegetable oil spray.
Place bread dough in pan and bake for 50 minutes.
Let cool.
Slice thin.

title: whole wheat pancakes(no fat recipe.)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in water and applesauce using a wire whisk.
Gently stir in beaten egg whites using wire whisk. (Add sliced strawberries, chopped apple or blueberries, if desired.)
Cook on hot griddle or waffle iron.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil water, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Let set 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until serving.
Heat to serve 1 cup or entire pot.

title: white gravy
directions: In small saucepan, melt margarine or butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more. Makes 3/4 cups (twelve one tablespoon) servings.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, 1 package pudding mix, 1 cup pineapple and 4 eggs in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Combine remaining 1 cup pineapple, 1 package pudding and Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread over cake.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time.

title: beanless nacho dip
directions: Brown
hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.	Add all other ingredients and stir until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: basil, tomato pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except penne.
Let marinate together at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Before serving, add cooked penne; let cool and serve at room temperature.
Add Romano or Parmesan to taste.
Enjoy!

title: lithuanian goulash
directions: Saute cabbage, ham and onion in cooking oil until tender. Parboil noodles; drain well.
Add to ham and cabbage mixture.

title: ruth's light blueberry muffins
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Add blended dry ingredients to cream mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit and cream
directions: Place all ingredients in blender on medium until smooth.

title: dee licious whole wheat bread
directions: Pour slightly cooled milk in bowl.
Add salt, oil, honey, water, eggs and yeast.
Add 3 cups of whole wheat flour and blend together.
Add 3 more cups of flour.
Knead with bread dough hooks 10 minutes.
Cover with a kitchen towel and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead once again with dough hook until dough appears smooth, no air bubbles.
Form into loaves and place in a well oiled bread pan.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Put bread in a cold oven.
Turn oven on to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
These loaves are very tender and Dee licious.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix everything together in casserole dish or any 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: creamy fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy, 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling over medium heat.
After about 3 minutes, drop a bit into cold water, if ball forms, remove from heat.
Place in baking dish; let cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes whole in the skins; peel and dice or pare, dice and cook them in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender; drain.
Pour hot dressing over hot potatoes.
Add scallions or onion and salt and mix carefully.
Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix together so there are no lumps.
Spread this out on a pizza pan and top with the lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening in flour and salt.
Mix together egg, vinegar and water.
Sprinkle over flour mixture.
Makes 2 small double crust pies or 1 big pie.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Add in flour and baking soda; mix well.
Gently add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake - part 2
directions: Prepare cake as directed for a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
After baking, poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon about 1-inch apart.
Pour caramel sauce over cake, then pour sweetened condensed milk over that; chill.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle broken bars on top.

title: basic honey gingerbread cookie dough
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, ginger, soda and salt. Beat butter in bowl with mixer until creamy.
Add sugar and honey and beat until smooth.
Add eggs; mix well.
With wooden spoon, beat in flour mixture, one cup at a time, until well blended. Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: In bowl, stir soup until smooth; blend in milk.
Stir in tuna, noodles, parsley and pimento.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: emily's favorite chicken
directions: Roll chicken jelly roll style around 2 or 3 slices dried beef. Wrap with bacon slices.
Secure with toothpicks.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Cover chicken completely with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve gravy over rice.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake until done in center.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400° till golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: sweet and sour chicken or pork
directions: Brown chicken or pork in oil.
Add garlic, green pepper and vinegar, sugar and pineapple with juice.
Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit smoothies
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill to blend flavors.

title: lazy day beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan (greased) and cover. Bake at 325° until beef is tender.
Check occasionally to see if more water is needed during baking.

title: herbed chicken breasts
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil and place chicken breasts on it, skin side up.
Salt lightly.
Cover each piece generously with sour cream and then sprinkle stuffing over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crispy batter for onion rings
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add water and beat until smooth with wooden spoon.
Dip onion rings in batter and then in crumbs. Deep fry until brown.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Roll in confectioners sugar and let stand in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: dessert surprise
directions: On a large cookie sheet, melt stick of butter.
Sprinkle on crushed graham crackers.
Then put 1 layer of chocolate chips and 1 layer of peanut butter chips.
Sprinkle coconut on top of chips. Pour condensed milk over everything on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until everything is melted and has a brownish top.

title: jimmy's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and mix in other ingredients.
Add fruit when custard is poured
into
cylinder.	You
do not cook this custard. This recipe
makes
enough
for
two freezers.
It will overflow when frozen in one freezer.

title: smoked sausage primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti by package directions.
Place sausage, vegetable and water in a 10-inch skillet.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 7 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add milk, butter and Italian seasoning to skillet.
Heat to melt butter.
Add sausage mixture with spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Let stand for 5 minutes to thicken.

title: kumquats and mandarins
directions: Drain mandarins and kumquats, reserve packing syrup in separate containers.
Finely chop mandarins.
Remove pits from the kumquats and finely chop.
Mix kumquats, mandarins and all remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Serve chilled as a dessert or as a side dish for poultry, pork or fish. Serves 2.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add ground chuck; brown and drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Grate cheese.
Mix yogurt, mayonnaise and cheese together and spread over cut sides of bread. Toast in preheated oven 10 minutes, until tops begin to brown and bubble.

title: stuffed garlic bread
directions: Pull bread from inside of French bread loaf to leave a shell and reserve bread in a bowl.
Brown ground beef and chopped onion. Add garlic powder, dill weed, oregano, salt and pepper to taste. Drain grease.
Mix shredded cheese with beef mixture until cheese melts.
Mix beef mixture with bread mixture and stuff into bread shell.
Wrap in tinfoil and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and pour melted margarine or butter mixed with garlic powder and dill weed across top and bake another 7 to 10 minutes, until crispy.
Serve immediately.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix together the sugar, water and coffee; bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour.
Cool.
Add the vodka and vanilla.
Bottle.
May be used immediately or store for future use.
Makes 7 cups.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, butter, vanilla, chocolate and nuts; mix well. Pour batter into an ungreased 9-inch square baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, melt margarine; add celery and onion and cook until tender over medium heat.
In another pan, prepare rice as directed on package.
In separate pan, cook broccoli as directed on package.
Add rice and broccoli to celery mixture.
Add soup; stir and cook over medium heat. Place in casserole dish and add Cheez Whiz.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: bohemian cheese buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar to yeast mixture. Add butter to flour mixture (flour and salt).
Add 3 yolks to yeast mixture, then light cream to yeast mixture.
Then add yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Place in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.
Invert soup plate over bowl.

title: kahlua
directions: Put sugar and coffee together.
Add boiling water.
Let cool to room temperature and add vodka and 1 vanilla bean per container.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in food processor or blender.
Set aside.
In bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk, pudding, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
In 9 x 9-inch dish, layer 1/2 cookies.
Pour pudding mixture evenly over crumbs (cookies).
Pour other half of cookies on top (save a few spoonfuls).
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining cookies on top.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar; add the remaining ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: avocado dip
directions: Grate avocados, tomatoes, onion and garlic in large bowl. Stir in picante sauce and sour cream. Top with grated cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Put into a greased brownie pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes (3 times recipe for 9 x 13 pan).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all this together.
Also, add salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain excess water. Mix spinach, cream cheese & can of soup with 1/2 can of onions. Spread in casserole dish. Cook on 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and put other 1/2 of onions on top. Put back in over for about 10 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Mix soups, milk, green pepper, onion and turkey in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cooked spaghetti and cheese (saving some cheese for the top).
Let simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Add mushrooms and stir well. Portion in casserole or serving dish; top with remaining cheese.
Cover and keep warm until serving time.
Great with leftover turkey.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave at High setting 8 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil and thickens, stirring every 2 minutes.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Immediately pour yolk mixture back into remaining hot mixture, blending thoroughly.
Microwave at High setting 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Fold in rice, butter and vanilla.
Mix in nutmeg and cinnamon to taste.
Add raisins, if desired.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer at least 4 hours.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in ice box to set up.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat altogether in mixer until mixed.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with Pam and put filling in it.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and cool 20 minutes.
While cake is cooling, make topping.

title: coconut pudding
directions: In saucepan heat the milk while mixing with a mixer the sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg.
Add beaten mixture to hot milk and cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and coconut.

title: japanese rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add chopped vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add rice, seasonings and soy sauce.
Simmer a while and let set about 10 minutes before serving.

title: baskin-robbins special
directions: Mix flour with butter.
Add nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 400° until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: sauce for sweet and sour pork
directions: In 10-inch skillet, pour in 1 tablespoon oil.
Heat 30 seconds on high heat.
Swirl oil in pan.
Heat another 30 seconds.
Turn heat down to moderate.
Add the garlic, then the green pepper and carrot and stir-fry for 2 or 3 minutes until vegetables darken somewhat in color.
Pour in 1/2 cup chicken, broth syrup, vinegar and soy sauce and bring to boil.
Boil rapidly for 1 minute. Immediately give the cornstarch/water mixture a quick stir to combine it and add it to the pan.
Cook a moment longer, stirring constantly.
When sauce is thick and clear, pour over fried pork and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with 1/2 cup melted butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Mix confectioners sugar with pineapple.
Cut bananas lengthwise; put over cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture over bananas.
Sprinkle pecans over top. Put maraschino cherries on top if desired.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in soda crackers and nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pull mixture up the sides of the pan with a spatula.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
When cooled, spread whipping cream over the meringue.
Top with pie filling.
You may substitute other fillings.
Excellent when strawberries are used.
Very pretty dessert for a special occasion dinner party.
Cut into squares.

title: mock apple pie(no apples needed)
directions: Prepare crust by spreading with Crisco and taking a fork to prick crusts.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pie shell.

title: tandy sheet cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, salt, flour, baking powder and butter together.
Spread on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot, spread with a thin coat of peanut butter.
Refrigerate until peanut butter hardens.
Melt chocolate; spread over top.
Cool.

title: prisnut
directions: Mix together eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add bacon, onions and cheese.
Pour into two 8 x 8 greased pans or one 9 x 13 pan. Bake approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.
Test with knife blade for doneness.
Cool, cut into squares.
Can be used as an appetizer or for breakfast or brunch.

title: oatmeal, walnuts and raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Stri in milk; sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop from tablespoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, for about 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes about 60.

title: marshmallow cookies
directions: Cook eggs, butter and sugar in double boiler 1/2 hour.
Stir until well-blended and then stir occasionally.
Let cook and add vanilla.
Grind up graham crackers.
Add to former mixture along with marshmallows and nuts.
Pack in large greased pan.
Let set in refrigerator overnight uncovered.
Cut in squares.

title: punch
directions: Combine Jell-O, boiling water and sugar; mix until dissolved. Add juices and water to total one gallon.
Add ginger ale when serving.
May be frozen to make slush.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and mix with soup and milk.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with 3 cups cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Great for breakfast, lunch or dinner.
Serves 8.

title: country cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup ham.
Mix all the ingredients well.
Shape into a ball and roll in the reserved ham.
Coat the ball completely.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix per package instructions.
Put half of mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate brittle sauce
directions: In quart casserole dish, combine morsels and butter. Microwave on High for 2 minutes and stir.
(Chocolate does not look melted until you stir it.)
Microwave on High for 2 minutes more.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in walnuts.
Serve over ice cream. (Sauce will harden when it hits the ice cream.)
Makes 2 cups.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all in a big pot, except the potatoes. Cook until meat is done, about 2 hours. Add the potatoes and cook 1 hour more.

title: fillings for strudel
directions: Mix egg yolks, cottage cheese, salt and raisins.
When mixed drop by tablespoonful unto pulled dough, rather close, drop cherries over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and buttered bread crumbs.
Roll and bake as directed on Strudel dough page.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Beat egg yolks briskly and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, salt and milk.
Whisk in lemon juice and rind.

title: boston cookies
directions: Mix butter until creamy; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and mix, then add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add water and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add cherries, juice, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: campers hot dish
directions: Put bacon in bottom of electric frying pan; heat until wilted.
Make small patties of ground round and put on top of bacon.
Sprinkle with Lawry's salt.
Slice vegetables on top of meat.
You can use as many vegetables as the family likes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put soup over this, then water. Let it simmer for several hours.
The longer the better.

title: vegetable meat stew
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
Roll into mixture of flour, salt, Accent and pepper.
Reserve flour mixture.
Brown meat slowly in hot oil. Sprinkle any remaining flour mixture over meat.
Toss to coat meat. Add onion; cook until limp.
Add water, garlic, bay leaf and thyme. Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and additional water as needed.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add peas and continue to cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Heat until steaming hot, but do not boil.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger corn hash
directions: Brown meat; drain off grease.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cracker or bread crumbs mixed with 1/4 stick of oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: black joe cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter or oil, then add the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is well dissolved.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan. Mix dry ingredients together. Add eggs and oil. Add mashed bananas and pecans last. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: elisen lebkuchen (ginger cookies)(nuremberger weisse lebkuchen)
directions: Beat well (1 hour by hand, 8 minutes with electric mixer) the eggs and sugar.
Add almonds, candied oranges and citron, spices and lemon rind.
Add flour a little at a time.
Spread the batter 1/2-inch thick on a layer of baking wafers.
Let dry overnight. Bake to a light golden brown at 300° (150°C) for 15 to 20 minutes. When cold, coat with white or chocolate icing.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons sugar, margarine and pretzels together and then spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple-oatmeal bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and add egg, vanilla and apple juice concentrate.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add thinly sliced apples, nuts, raisins and oatmeal.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan evenly in pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut into 20 squares.

title: chile zucchini bread
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour dry ingredients into top 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf tins (2).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; then add pineapple, bananas, strawberries and nuts.
Mix together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish and let jell.
Then spread sour cream over jelled mixture, followed by remaining mixture and jell.
Keep chilled and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store in covered container.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons to cup of hot water.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the other ingredients and beat until smooth. Bake 1 1/2 hours in tube pan or 2 loaf pans lined with waxed paper.

title: basic ground beef mixture
directions: In large skillet, combine all ingredients. Cook and stir over medium heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender; drain. Cool. Freeze in three 2 c. portions. Makes 3 pints. * We often make this in the fall by making 5 or 6 times the recipe and put it in the freezer for winter.

title: choco-marshmallow cookies
directions: Top with Cocoa Frosting.

title: paula's blushing peaches
directions: Place 1 peach half in 6 dessert dishes. Heat all ingredients, except whipped topping.
Stir constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Cool.
Top each peach with whipped topping.
Pour cooled sauce over peach halves.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Mix half of the cake mix (dry), the margarine, brown sugar, water and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Heat frosting in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until thin.
Drizzle over top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts.
Cool completely; cut into 1 1/4-inch squares.
Makes 35 squares.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine the first 4 ingredients and 1 cup of cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup of milk; pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients and add the crabmeat which has been picked over. Gently mix in the crabmeat.
Form into 6 to 8 crab cakes and cover with corn flake crumbs.
Fry in a buttered pan until golden.

title: oprah's corn chowder
directions: Preheat a large, heavy saucepan over medium heat for about 1 minute.
Spray it twice with the oil.
Saute onion for 5 minutes or until translucent.
Add 4 cups corn and saute for 4 to 5 minutes, until it softens a bit.
Add 2 cups broth and cook 20 minutes or until corn is very tender.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package.
Let thicken slightly.
Add crushed pineapple and shredded carrots.
Chill until set.
Serve on lettuce.

title: baked cranberries and apples casserole
directions: Mix together and put in dish.

title: special pea salad
directions: In large bowl combine peas, pecans, onion, water chestnuts and pimento.
Mix well.
Mix together the oil, vinegar and sugar and spread evenly over mixture; refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, drain mixture and stir in mayonnaise.
Serve in bowl lined with lettuce leaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in order as given and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in large mixing bowl.
Add berries.
Put in refrigerator until jello starts to set.
Push cake into jello. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Jello and strawberries are on outside; cake is on inside.
Delicious!

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour melted mixture over whole box of cereal in a large bowl.
Stir to coat. Shake coated cereal in a paper bag containing the powdered sugar. Spread powdered sugar coated cereal mixture on waxed paper to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans well and mix with soup and onion.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in 9 x 13 pan; place chicken on top.
Drizzle with margarine.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and baking powder.
Then add the nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350°.
Insert wire tester and when it comes out dry, it is done.

title: coconut carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cook in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack; frost.

title: easy dessert
directions: Spread pie filling and pineapple in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan. Cover fruit evenly with cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans evenly on top.
Top evenly with pats of butter or margarine.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8 - 10.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Then, mix nuts and chocolate bits together.
Mix.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Heat milk, add 2 teaspoons butter; set aside.
Beat eggs until lemon-colored with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and remaining sugar to egg mixture; mix well.
Batter will be thin. Bake in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan for 15 or 20 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from oven and immediately spread with peanut butter, carefully.
Refrigerate until peanut butter is hard.
Melt chocolate bars and spread on top of the peanut butter.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: flour and egg sponge cake
directions: Beat together egg yolks and water 5 minutes with rotary beater.
Add sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Sift together flour and salt.
Stir gradually into egg yolk mixture, keeping the mixture smooth. Blend in lemon extract.
Beat until frothy 4 egg whites. Add cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff enough to hold a peak.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes in slow oven (325°).
Invert pan and cool.
Remove from pan.

title: san antonio-style chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in half at joints.
Discard tips.
Combine picante sauce, catsup and honey.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, turning once.
Take chicken out of marinade and place on broiler pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Baste with marinade, turn and bake, brushing with marinade every 10 minutes until tender; about 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut into serving pieces.
Brown in oil in skillet; drain.
Place in stockpot with water to cover. Add salt, pepper and onion.
Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender.
Combine flour and 1 teaspoon salt in medium bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in eggs and enough milk to make soft dough.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Remove chicken from stockpot, reserving stock.
Set aside.
Bring reserved chicken stock to a boil.
Drop in dumplings, one at a time.
Cook for 20 minutes or until tender. Return chicken to stockpot.
Simmer until heated through.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Cream together until fluffy the shortening, sugar and eggs. Beat 5 minutes at high speed on mixer or by hand.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Mix in alternately with water and vanilla, using low speed on mixer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: maryland hot crab dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and horseradish until smooth.
Add scallions, dill, paprika and lemon juice; stir well. Gently fold in crabmeat.
Pour into buttered souffle dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
