Serve at once with tostados.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine and blend oil, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Squeeze excess juice from kraut.
Cut kraut some if it is the shredded kind. Place kraut in large bowl and loosen with a fork; add chopped vegetables.
Pour the oil, sugar, vinegar and salt mixture over the kraut mixture.
Cover bowl and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
The longer this salad stands, the better it tastes.
This will keep in the refrigerator for 2 or 3 weeks.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and roll in balls.
Add soup and 1 can water over meatballs.
Bake in dish at 350° until done.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar, then add eggs.
Sift together the first seven ingredients and add alternately to the sugar mixture with the sherry.
Add nuts, raisins, dates and figs. Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry into patties.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Blend flour into oil, stirring constantly over medium heat and brown.
Add water gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Add shrimp last.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice with crackers.
Very, very good.

title: broccoli capellini
directions: Saute broccoli in olive oil until al dente.
Add garlic, peppers, basil, salt and pepper.
Stir 1 minute.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer until capellini are tender.
Toss pasta with sauce. Sprinkle with cheese and toss lightly.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
In mixing bowl, combine the chilled Jell-O and pudding.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed; chill until mixture mounds when spooned.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into a 7 or 8 cup mold.
Chill until firm or overnight.
Makes 10 or 12 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer onions, garlic and peppers in olive oil until onions are golden in color.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Just simmer on low heat for at least an hour or a little longer is better.
Don't let it bubble too much just a slow simmer.
Add water if too thick.

title: spicy cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, liver, mustard, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add crumbs and egg; mix well.
Shape into one-inch balls, using rounded teapoon measure for each.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomato into small pieces.
Finely slice green onions, including tops.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Allow flavors to blend overnight.

title: rice 'n sausage stir
directions: Brown
sausage; drain.
Add onions.
Cook until tender. Stir in
water and oregano; bring to full boil.
Stir in rice and parsley (if used).
Cover, remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes then fluff with fork.
Stir in processed cheese spread until melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, onion, green peppers and celery together.
Remove chicken from stock; strain stock.
Cook spaghetti in stock; drain. Reserve stock.
Add cubed chicken to cooked spaghetti.
Add tomato sauce and soup and blend.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
If dry, add some stock.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 16.
Halve ingredients for family.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers and chips.

title: cheddar biscuit cups
directions: In a small bowl, combine the flour and cheese. Stir in milk and mayonnaise, just until moistened.
Fill 5 greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Fill empty cup halfway with water. Bake at 425° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bowl with a lid.
Add meat and shake.
Brown meat in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Pour over meat and add Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms. Simmer for 2 hours.
Add sour cream.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: open-faced sandwiches
directions: Layer 1 slice of turkey, 1 slice ham, 1 slice tomato and 1 spear broccoli on each muffin half.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° until firm and brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine the cauliflower, garbanzo beans, celery and chopped onion.
In small bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over cauliflower mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill 3 to 24 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add lemon juice slowly. Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Place into baking dish with little water.
Microwave just until crisp; drain. Combine tomatoes with eggs.
Pour over cauliflower.
Spoon soup over tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano over soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until custard is set.

title: griffin's barbecue sauce
directions: This sauce is wonderful over spare ribs cooked either over charcoal or in oven.
Combine tomato sauce, wine vinegar, minced onion, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed, dry sherry, salt, pepper, garlic, and Griffin's Waffle Syrup.
Combine all ingredients and use to baste ribs as they cook.

title: aunt jane's pumpkin pie
directions: Melt butter and put in a large mixing bowl.
Empty pumpkin into bowl.
(Use the pumpkin can to measure milk.)
Pour the canned milk into the pumpkin can and add enough regular milk to make 3/4 can full.
Pour into bowl and mix with mixer on low speed.
Continue to add the remaining ingredients until all are mixed well.
You can add more spices, if desired.
Pour into pie shells (2 to 3) and bake on 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a shallow bowl or pie pan, combine the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
In another shallow bowl, beat together the egg and water.
Dip the eggplant slices in the egg mixture, then into the crumb mixture.
Place the slices in a single layer in the prepared baking dish.
Drizzle the oil over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden and tender.
Pour the tomato sauce over the eggplant, then sprinkle with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake another 7 to 10 minutes or until the cheese has melted.
Serve with a lettuce and tomato salad and crusty bread.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Cooking time: 37 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil whole cabbage in pot of water.
Slowly peel whole leaves off as they become pliable.
In a large bowl, mix together ground beef, green pepper, onion and rice.
With leaves still warm, wrap around meat mixture and secure with a toothpick.

title: walnut-crab spread
directions: Combine crabmeat and cheese.
Blend in onion, lemon juice and salt.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts, mixing well.
Turn mixture out on foil.
Shape into 4 logs.
Roll into remaining nuts until surface is well coated.
Chill until firm.
This freezes very well.
Recipe makes enough for 2 boxes crackers.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the 2 candies together in a double boiler or microwave. Stir in the peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix until fluffy and spread on cooled 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake. Halve recipe to frost an 8 or 9-inch square cake.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, spices and vanilla.
Fold in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mix sugar, spices and salt.
If apples are very tart, use additional sugar (up to 1 cup).
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Put in 1/3 of the crumbs, then half of the apples.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat.
Mix water, lemon juice and rind; pour over.
Put on remaining crumbs and dot with butter. Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Combine with beaten egg.
Stir rhubarb into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cover with another crust or lattice crust.
Bake in 400° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: brownie delight
directions: Cook brownies as directed on package.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Mix 3/4 of Cool Whip with pudding.
Layer brownies, Cool Whip pudding mixture and repeat until all is used.
Top with layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bar and top with cherries.
Use a decorative see through bowl for effect.

title: white bean and tuna salad sandwich
directions: Stir together first 11 ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve on lightly toasted bread with lettuce.

title: all in one quiche
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a blender and mix well.
Turn into an ungreased 9 or 10-inch pie or quiche pan.
Add meat or shellfish, poking into the batter.
Top with onions, mushrooms and cheese.
Bake until top is golden, about 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white until stiff. Add brown sugar and pecans. Drop on buttered cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: russell's chicken
directions: Place seasoned chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 450° oven.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add everything else to pan except broth.
Bring broth to boil before adding to pan.
Stir together.
Place chicken over rice in pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until rice is cooked and chicken is tender.

title: hot dog stew
directions: Brown hot dogs in oil, onions and garlic also.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Let simmer until desired thickness.
Add cabbage 1/2 hour before you add potatoes.
Add all ingredients and cook until potatoes are done.
Keep ingredients covered while cooking cabbage, then uncovered for potatoes and rest of ingredients.

title: baked vidalia onion dip
directions: Combine Swiss cheese, onion and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Lightly grease baking pan; add cheese/onion mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 cups. Serve with assorted crackers, breads or chips.

title: my mom's squash pickles
directions: Place squash, peppers, pimento and onions in a large container; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Wash well to remove salt; drain.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add vanilla extract, baking powder, dates and pecans. Pour in greased tube pan. Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 300°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Place macaroni in a 2-quart pan of boiling water with a dash of salt.
Let cool for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain macaroni.
Pour in a mixing bowl with diced, cooked ham, cheese, green pepper, butter and milk.
Stir vigorously and pour into a casserole dish (about 8 x 11 x 2-inch) and cover with glass lid.
Let cook in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Garnish with parsley and ready to serve.
Will serve 6 to 8 adults.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Mix cabbage and salt together and let stand 30 minutes. Squeeze out all the liquid.
Heat butter or margarine in deep skillet; add cabbage, sugar and pepper.
Cook over low heat until cabbage is done, stirring very frequently.
Add noodles and toss to blend.

title: red hot salsa
directions: In blender or food processor fitted with steel blade, process tomatoes, chiles and garlic until coarsely chopped.
Turn into medium-size bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Spicy and light, great with tortillas, guacamole, chips and grilled hamburgers.

title: pizza supreme cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and mozzarella.
Beat until well blended. Add remaining ingredients except pecans. Beat until well mixed. Shape into a large ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Cover with plastic wrap until serving time.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in Pammed Pyrex dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: chelly dogs
directions: Use same size chili and jelly jars.
Heat until hot dogs are tender.
Can be cooked in a crock-pot.
Can substitute little smoked sausages for the hot dogs.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine white sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters and coat with mixture. Drop quarters into Bundt pan.
Melt butter and add brown sugar. Keep stirring until carmel-like.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: malted milk balls
directions: Add enough melted white chocolate to the vanilla malted milk to form a very dry ball.
Set in refrigerator until it crystallizes. Dip in melted coating chocolate.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Scald milk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cardamom.

title: mayonnaise sauce
directions: Mix sugar and flour; gradually add water and vinegar.
Cook until flour thickens mixture and doesn't taste floury.
Add mustard immediately.
Cool slightly and add 1 1/2 cups store mayonnaise. Good dressing for garden lettuce, potato salad, macaroni salad, etc.
Especially good on layered salad.
Be sure and add 1/4 cup mustard; it gives the flavor.

title: nachos
directions: Fry beans in small amount of shortening; toast or fry tortillas.
Spread beans on tortillas.
Place on baking pan.
Add peppers and top with cheese.
Bake in 425° to 450° oven for about 3 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix in pecans, vanilla and flour.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hobo stacks
directions: Cover rectangular cookie sheet with 2 layers of aluminum foil. Season meat with salt, pepper and soy sauce as desired.
Shape into large patties and place on pan.
Top each patty with sliced potatoes, carrots, onions and 1 pat of butter.
Cover hobo stacks with aluminum foil and seal edges. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate.
Serve with taco shells.

title: tangy cheesy salsa dip
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef together and drain.
Break or dice cheese into a large bowl and put in microwave on Medium-high until melted.
Mix meat with melted cheese and add salsa.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, with cooked noodles. Place in a baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake until bubbly hot, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: baked apricots
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Alternate a layer of crushed crackers with drained apricots, brown sugar and a dash of cinnamon.
When layers are completed, pour butter and apricot juice over the top. Bake in a preheated oven at 300°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cream all ingredients except potatoes and cheese.
Mix in saucepan over low heat till well blended.
Stir in potatoes. Spread into a 13x9-inch glass baking dish, spread cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cooked clear through.

title: summer berry cornmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Combine yogurt, milk, eggs and butter in mixing bowl.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients.
Stir in berries just until combined. Divide batter among 12 buttered 2 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Sprinkle each muffin with some of the orange sugar and place pan in oven. Reduce oven temperature to 400°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins are golden.
Cool muffins in pan on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Remove muffins from pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and corn meal.
Add onion. Combine egg and milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop mixture from a teaspoon into hot oil and fry until lightly browned.

title: grilled venison steaks
directions: Slice venison in steaks and season.
Wrap a bacon strip around each steak; hold with toothpicks.
Place in bowl and pour Italian dressing over meat.
Marinate for 24 hours.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Wash cabbage; discard any wilted or discolored leaves. Cut cabbage in eighths and remove core in each section. Shred cabbage and carrots in a food processor until finely chopped. Place in a mixing bowl and blend in dressing.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, keeping 2 tablespoons of the liquid.
Mix salmon, egg and onion in mixing bowl until mixture is sticky. Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to the 2 tablespoons of reserved liquid.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into small patties, using hands.

title: french onion soup(easy)
directions: Saute onions in butter until brown; add broth and pepper. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in soup bowls; top with toasted French bread and cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: You will need round toothpicks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer in small bowl.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, butter, peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: brunch quiche
directions: Mix together the eggs, beaten with salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, milk, onion and green pepper. Mix well.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, sugar, eggs, biscuit mix, margarine and vanilla in blender. Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Sprinkle on the coconut. Bake 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool on a wire rack. Serves 8.

title: grandma chapman's macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 pyrex baking dish.
Grate 4 cups cheddar cheese.
Cook noodles as directed. A layer of noodles first, salt and pepper (a pinch will do).
Cover with layer of cheese, pour milk up to the level of 1st layer.
Repeat above for 2nd layer. Cook in 400° or 425° oven for 40 - 50 minutes.
Cool and enjoy! Serve with coleslaw and warm buttered dark rye bread.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel avocado, remove pit and mash.
Blend in other ingredients and beat until light and creamy.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in 1 teaspoon bacon grease for 10 minutes.
Drain. Layer 1/2 of beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of green peas; dot with butter and add onions.
Repeat layers.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle onion rings on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together ground beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls.
Place soup in baking dish and add balls.
Spoon soup over balls.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until done at 350°. After 1/2 hour or so, uncover and turn balls so they don't dry out.
Good with mashed potatoes.

title: aunt joni's chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch wide strips (after rinsing and trimming away any fat).
In bowl, stir together with whisk or fork the cornstarch, flour, baking powder, salt, pepper, water and egg.
Mix in basil and minced garlic clove.
Heat oil (2 to 3 inches deep) in large pot.
When oil is hot, place several of the chicken strips (after dipping into the batter) into the oil.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat until all chicken is batter dipped and fried.
(You can also use this batter to deep-fry zucchini, carrots, mushrooms, onions, etc.) Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix egg and sugar, then add juice and boil 3 minutes.
Add jello and boil 5 minutes.
Cool good.
Add whipped cream and mix good.
Put in pie shell.
Chill.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix egg yolk and cream cheese together with hand mixer.
Cut of crust of white bread and discard.
Roll white bread flat with rolling pin.
Spread egg/cheese mixture thinly onto the flattened bread.
Roll up.
Put sugar and some cinnamon in a bowl and stir to mix.
Dip rolled bread into melted butter.
Then roll in sugar mixture.
Line up on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut into thirds.
Makes about 69 pieces.
Serve with sour cream.
Use toothpicks to lift.
Can be used as appetizer or dessert.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Ask the butcher to cut some chops at least 1-inch thick and make a slit for stuffing.
Mix well about a half cup per chop of croutons, egg, chopped onions, garlic, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Stuff into opening.
Rub oil on each side of chop and place in skillet with small amount of oil added.
Brown on both sides being careful to keep stuffing intact.
Place on baking pan and put in 350° oven until stuffing is done.
These should be turned over at least once.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce, oregano, macaroni and salt to taste. Pack in loaf pan; top with remaining tomato sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinade
directions: Great for marinating lamb or beef.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape in balls and cook 25 minutes at 300°.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour into baking dish.
Add cherries on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.
May use peaches, apples or blueberries.

title: viv criner's pumpkin apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
In a medium bowl combine eggs, oil and pumpkin with electric mixer.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Beat on low speed until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased and floured Bundt pan (I spray it with Baker's Joy, works like a dream).
Bake 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan. When completely cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Great in the fall with coffee.

title: holiday raspberry salad
directions: Make jello mixture:
Combine jello, boiling water and raspberries; pour into flat dish or mold.
Set.
Mix in a separate bowl the sour cream and marshmallows.
Let set an hour or so.
Beat with mixer.
Spread on top of jello mixture.
Set.
Great holiday salad.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder together.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat well. Add crushed blackberries.
Alternate sour milk and dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Brown sausage in skillet until crumbled; remove sausage, draining excess fat.
Saute onion in sausage fat.
Combine sausage, onion and seasonings to taste; add beans.
Pour into 14 x 10 x 2-inch roasting pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 20 to 24 servings.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Take Cool Whip and pudding mix and mix them together until creamy.
Then add fruit cocktail and mix together and there you have your Cool Whip Delight.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in thin slices.
Arrange in pie plate.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° about an hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in ovenproof dish.
Top with shredded cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until heated through.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients only until well blended.
Do not overmix. Best to let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer hamburger, pepperoni, sauce, cheese, spaghetti, hamburger, pepperoni, sauce and cheese in cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add water, bouillon cubes and salts and pepper.
Bring to a boil and dissolve cubes.
Add noodles and boil 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and boil 4 minutes.
Add milk and Velveeta.
Melt cheese and serve.

title: spanish style chicken and sausage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add sausage and brown well, about 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add chicken, onion and green pepper and cook 5 minutes longer.
Meanwhile, dissolve bouillon cubes in water; stir in salt, thyme and garlic powder.
Pour into skillet.
Add peas and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and tomatoes.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: charoseth
directions: Core apples (it is not necessary to peel them).
Chop apples and walnuts together in food processor or blender or by hand until finely chopped.
With a wooden spoon, stir in the cinnamon, honey and wine.
This will serve 10 to 12 people when serving 1 teaspoon or 1 tablespoon per person on a piece of matzoh.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Now mix 1 tube of crushed Ritz crackers and 1 stick margarine.
Spread on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Blend in cooked broccoli.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Melt margarine; add crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over the top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach lightly; drain well.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, onions, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Add spinach to mixture.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: breakfast overnight omelet
directions: Combine all ingredients the night before. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight. Bake in the morning at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: bun-steads
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buns.
Fill buns; wrap each bun separately in foil.
Bake at 250° about 30 minutes, until filling is heated and cheese melts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In an oblong pan, spread sliced peaches.
Add dry cake mix to top of peaches, using fork to break up any lumps.
Add pats of butter all over top until you use the whole stick.
Put in oven at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: harvest zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salt water until barely tender. Drain well.

title: play dough
directions: Cook on medium. Add food coloring before it becomes thick.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill in a square dish.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook contents of rice and seasoning packets according to directions on package.
While rice is cooking, melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken and rice.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Mix sour cream, sugar and Cool Whip. Wash and quarter strawberries.
Mix with glaze.
Layer cake.
Layer sour cream mixture.
Layer strawberry.
Continue until complete. Top with strawberry.

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Place cottage cheese in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Slice eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks.
Mash 2 yolks.
Reserve remaining yolks for another use.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients. Pipe into egg whites.
If desired, garnish with paprika and parsley. Yields 10 servings.

title: saucy chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring frequently, until firm and white.
Sprinkle salt over chicken. Add water and contents of rice and seasoning packets.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add warm milk and water.
Beat on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour (batter will be stiff).
Do not knead.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, celery and cheese and shape into a log while rolling over nuts (on waxed paper).
Garnish with parsley and serve with crackers.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add sauce and juice.
Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Top with Colby cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13 -inch pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Put shortening in the mixing bowl first, then add light brown sugar.
Beat 1/4 of a minute, then add the granulated sugar. Scrape the sides of the bowl as soon as the mixture tends to stay there.
Use high speed when beating the sugars.
Beat both sugars with the shortening about 1 minute, then add egg.
After the egg is beaten in, add the vanilla.
All of this is on high speed. Now, beat these ingredients for 4 minutes on high speed.
Scrape the sides of the bowl after 1 to 2 minutes.
At the end of 4 minutes, the batter should be light in color and fluffy.
And by the end of the mixing of flour and chips that fluffiness should still be there.
Don't overblend.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jackie's favorite brisket
directions: Place brisket in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix evenly over the meat.
Spoon can of cranberries evenly over the soup mix and beef.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (or at least 20 minutes per pound).
Makes a tasty and tender beef brisket and lots of gravy to serve over noodles or Kasha.
Also, this dish smells fabulous while it's cooking!

title: sangria
directions: Slice lemons, oranges and limes in thin slices and squeeze for juice.
Pour sugar over the slices.
Combine the lemons, oranges, limes, sugar and Cointreau and put in glass container.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Pour in wine and club soda and add ice.

title: chicken elder
directions: In 9 x 9-inch dish, melt butter; mix well with crushed crackers.
Add chopped chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken; add few cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: frosted cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients. Combine flour, cocoa & soda together. Add flour mixture alternately with milk to the mixed 3 ingredients. Drop by tsp. on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°. When cool, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt
cup
margarine and pour in greased casserole dish. Combine
all
ingredients
except
dressing mix and 1/2 stick margarine.
Place
in casserole dish.
Combine dressing mix and melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
May put part of topping in bottom of casserole.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. As it thickens, add egg yolks. Cook until thick. Remove from heat; add 2 tsp. of vanilla. Pour into a baked deep dish pie crust.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Beat white and brown sugar.
Stir egg, vanilla, salt, baking soda and flour.

title: mom schroeder's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Combine sugar, salt and spices.
Blend egg mixture into pumpkin; mix well.
Blend in sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into two pastry shells.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° to 350° and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pies are done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: vegetable rice mold
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine vegetables and heat for a few minutes.
Combine with rice.
In a separate container, combine next three ingredients.
Gradually add olive oil and stir until well blended.
Pour over salad and toss gently. Spoon mixture into mold coated with vegetable cooking spray. Chill 10 minutes.
Invert onto lettuce leaves.
Garnish with tomato rose or sweet pepper flower.

title: saucy chicken and pasta dinner
directions: Heat 1/4 cup of the spread in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup spread, mushrooms and peas.
Cook 2 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in hot, cooked noodles and cheese until cheese is melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix in order given (use jello as it comes from package). Refrigerate for several hours.
Using approximately 1 level teaspoon of mixture, form a strawberry (vary the size as real strawberries).
Roll each in red sugar.
Insert stem (available at bakery supply store).

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water until soft.
Drain.
Add margarine.
Add enough crushed saltines to thicken.
Put mixture in an 8 x 8-inch buttered casserole.

title: linguine with clams and basil
directions: Open clams and save their juices to flavor pasta.
Coarsely chop clams and refrigerate.
There should be about 1/3 cup clams and up to 2/3 cup juice.
Pour juice into pot with about 6 cups water and some salt and bring to boil.
Add linguine, stirring until desired degree of doneness.
As pasta cooks, heat half and half to simmer in small saucepan.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet and add garlic.
Cook briefly, stirring and add clams and hot half and half.
Remove from heat.
When linguine is done, drain and return to pot.
Add remaining butter and toss to coat strands.
Add clam mixture, basil, cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: vegetable and turkey sandwiches
directions: Combine green pepper slices, cauliflower, carrot strips, chopped tomatoes, olive slices and onion strips. Stir in Italian salad dressing and basil. Cover and refrigerate vegetable mixture for 4 to 24 hours.

title: bolognese sauce for pasta
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; drain fat.
Add carrots, onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients (except pasta).
Cover and cook for no less than 20 minutes (flavor improves as sauce simmers).
Prepare pasta. Serve sauce over hot cooked pasta.

title: mexican pie
directions: Pat one can crescent rolls out in bottom of pie plate to make crust.
Add drained meat mixture.
Cover with very thin sliced and peeled fresh tomatoes.
Add chopped green chilies.
Add grated cheese to top of this mixture in pie plate.

title: peach pancakes
directions: Add chopped peaches to pancake mix. Add a little peach juice to water to make a thick batter. Cook in skillet until done.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill before using.

title: white confetti fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the white chocolate with the milk. Remove from heat
and stir in the salt, vanilla and cherries. Spread onto wax paper lined pan, 8 x 9-inch.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Spread over sweet potato mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Brown meat and place in a casserole with all other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Lower the temperature to 300° and bake for 2 hours.
Garnish with: green pepper, green onion, chopped tomato and sour cream.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown sausage meat and drain.
Then put back on stove and melt cheese in sausage.
Take cheese and sausage mixture and spread on bread.
Sprinkle a little rosemary on each.
Place in oven to toast bread.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; cool.
Prick brownies with fork and pour Kahlua over them and let soak in. Whip up Jell-O chocolate mousse according to package directions. Break Skor or Heath bars into small pieces.
Break up half of the brownies and place in the bottom of a glass trifle dish.
Cover with half of the mousse, layer with half of the candy and then add half of the whipped topping.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients.

title: aunt patsy's four reds side dish
directions: Microwave pierced potatoes 15 minutes on High.
Halve potatoes and place in broiling pan.
Add onions and tomatoes, cut-side up. Set in peppers, skin-side up.
Add garlic.
Sprinkle with olive oil, salt and pepper.
Broil close to element until potatoes are browned and peppers are blistered, turning all vegetables often. Cook about 15 minutes.
If onions and garlic aren't soft and gold, cook 10 to 15 minutes more at 450°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald 3 1/2 cups milk in a double boiler.
Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add to milk.
Add syrup and salt.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup of milk and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add to double boiler and cook until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir constantly while cooking.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine corn syrup and cream. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate. Stir until completely melted. Serve warm as a dip for fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups fondue.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut 1/4-inch slice off one end of each tomato (slice from end without stem).
With a tiny spoon, scoop out and discard seeds and pulp (a 1/4 teaspoon works well here).
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Fill tomatoes with olive mixture, mounding slightly.
Chill.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar for pastry.
Spread pastry in 8-inch square pan (pat with fingers).
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Mix rest of ingredients with eggs.
Spread over baked pastry for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: vort limpa favorite christmas bread
directions: Mix stout or ale, anise seed and shortening in saucepan; heat to lukewarm.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, orange rind, syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups white flour and 1 cup rye flour.
Beat until smooth.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to first mixture.
Beat until thoroughly mixed; add remaining flour. Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and satiny (elastic to the touch) using only enough flour to keep from sticking to hands.
This must be done quickly, but thoroughly. Place in well-greased large bowl.
Turn dough over to grease both sides of dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Putting bowl over warm (not too hot) water quickens rising.
Let rise about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Shape into two loaves about 12-inches long.
Place in greased pans.
Can be baked on large cookie sheet, greased; grease between loaves, place loaves close together.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven preheated to 350° about 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven at once and turn out on cloth covered board.
Brush lightly with hot water.
Cover and let cool.
This recipe came from Sweden.
Seems complicated, but very simple once you've made it.

title: mundle bread cookies
directions: Mix all together and shape like a loaf.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: biscuit and ham bake
directions: In a large skillet, place butter and add onion and mushrooms. Cook until tender.
Stir in flour, parsley, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Add hot water and bouillon granules.
Mix well.
Stir in tomatoes and ham.
Cook and stir 10 minutes.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Stir just until moistened.
Add cheese and drop by spoonfuls onto ham mixture.
Bake, uncovered, until biscuits are deep golden brown and filling is bubbly, 20 minutes or so.

title: mama's surprise
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
After baking, let it cool. Melt ice cream until stirable.
Mix melted ice cream and crumbled cake together.
Put in a cake pan.
Put in freezer until hard.
Cut in squares, pour syrup over, spread on whipped cream and top with a cherry.

title: baked chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut four (18 x 12-inch) sheets heavy-duty aluminum foil and coat each sheet with cooking spray.
Arrange 1/4 of sliced onion evenly in center of each sheet of foil.
Top each with a chicken breast half.
Spread 1 teaspoon mustard over each breast half and sprinkle evenly with salt and pepper.
Top each with 1/4 of squash, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Sprinkle evenly with basil and garlic.
Dot each with 1 teaspoon margarine.
Fold edges of foil over and wrap securely.
Place packets on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve in foil packets.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla and let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Mix flour mixture alternately with oil mixture until well blended.
Add apples and pecans.

title: coconut lust
directions: Pour butter over flour, make a crust, place nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: minnie's old fashioned stock pot
directions: Cut meat that is slightly frozen into cubes.
Cook in hot, melted shortening until brown.
Add water, salt and soup bones. Heat to boiling on surface temperature of 375° to 400°.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour on medium.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Marinate
chicken 2 hours or more. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice, thaw and drain strawberries.
Heat the juice and add to hot water and pour over jello.
Then when jello is dissolved well, add ice cream, then the sliced strawberries,
Place in the refrigerator until mixture starts to jell well, then pour into a baked pie shell.
Later top with whipped cream.
Sounds delicious!

title: mom's apple dumplings
directions: Chip apples up into small chips; roll biscuits one at a time out to be very thin.
Put chipped apples in center of biscuits. Add 1 tablespoon sugar, 1 teaspoon butter and a little nutmeg or cinnamon.
Fold edge of biscuit over all of the ingredients.
Put folded side down in baking dish.
Finish all the rolled dough and put in pan.
Sprinkle any chipped apples left on top of dumplings. Sprinkle sugar well over the top of them.
Add nutmeg or cinnamon and dot with butter.
Pour boiling water on top of all this until almost to the top of dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top of dough is lightly browned.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in large shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Serves 8.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits as directed.
To grits add butter, eggs, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with crushed red pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vichyssoise(cold potato soup)
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp and clear.
Add potatoes, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Blend in blender.
Cool.
Add milk and cream.
Chill overnight.
If it becomes too thick, add more milk and serve.
Garnish with chopped parsley or green onion tops.
Serves 8.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Bake
cake
mix
as
directed on box.
Crumble cake and fold in remaining ingredients.
Pack tightly in Bundt cake pan lined with
wax paper.
To decorate, put red and green candied cherries and pecan halves on top.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease some cookie sheets.
Cream the butter and peanut butter together.
Beat in the 2 sugars, then add egg, water and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: mexi casserole
directions: Combine first three ingredients. Cook until tender and brown. Combine next seven ingredients.
Simmer on top of meat mixture for ten minutes.
Put half in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of the tortilla chips, then cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork medallions with red onion confit
directions: Sear the medallions in a saute pan on both sides and finish them in the oven.
Combine the vinegar and the jus de veau lie in a saucepan; bring to a quick boil.
Remove from the heat.
Deglaze the saute pan with the vinegar and jus de veau lie.
Bring it to a boil.
Keep it warm or reheat at time of service.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pineapple, gelatine, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted oleo.
Save 2/3 cup for topping.
Spread rest in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: bun bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Add salted peanuts. Put 1/2 mixture in a buttered jelly roll pan.
Cool.
Save the other half.
Mix vanilla pudding with evaporated milk and vanilla. Add melted butter and powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Spread on top of cooled chocolate layer.
Carefully spread other half of chocolate on top of pudding mixture.
Cool.
Cut in small bars. Keep refrigerated.

title: beef curry with onions
directions: Stir curry powder in the center of a large, heavy frying pan over heat.
When hot, add garlic.
Mash and stir in a little oil at a time.
Add salt, pepper and ginger; mix well.
Add meat and onions; stir and cook until onions are tender.
Add soy sauce and bouillon.
Cover pan, bring to boil and cook until meat is tender.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: * If making ahead ahead, use raw noodles and refrigerate for 8 hours.
If not, use partially cooked noodles.

title: red sauce
directions: Cook a few hours, until thick, on low heat.
Stir often.
Seal in pint jars (hot).

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix together.
Let sit for 6 hours or longer until very bubbly.

title: "better than sex" cake(not mom's)
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Poke holes all through cake (after cake is cool).
Pour milk all over cake.
Cool in fridge 1 hour.
Pour caramel over cake.
Cool in fridge overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Skor bars.

title: rocky mountain rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and chill.
Season to taste.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in shallow dish.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice on chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn chicken once; marinate with juices several times.
Serve with rice.
Do not overbake, chicken will be dry.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thickened.
Add eggs and sugar; mix well and reheat until thick, stirring constantly. Let cool, then add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade mounds
directions: Gradually mix first 3 ingredients until doughy. Add coconut and pecans. Mix thoroughly. Roll into bite size balls. Lay out on a cookie sheet (makes 130). Refrigerate until firm.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters, save broth.
Heat Pyrex casserole with butter. When melted and hot, drop oysters in and layer with celery mixed with spices and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: marinated pork tenderloins, best on grill
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Trim fat from tenderloins; place tenderloins in a large shallow nonmetal dish.
Pour molasses mixture over tenderloins, cover with plastic wrap and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight, turning meat at least twice.

title: company rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 cup warm milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Dissolve salt and rest of sugar in milk.
Add yeast mixture, then add 4 cups flour; beat well.
Add beaten eggs and shortening; beat 3 minutes.
Add remaining flour and knead until smooth (do not make dough too stiff).
Let rise twice.

title: fluffy yellow pineapple marshmallow cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold egg whites in.
Bake in 3 waxed paper-lined 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 45 minutes.
Bone and put into a baking dish. Pour cream of celery soup over chicken.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown meat in drippings; remove meat. Add flour and brown to a dark color. Add onions, parsley and garlic and cook until soft. Add water and rice. Add salt, pepper and meat. Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 1 hour, covered. When rice is done, uncover and cook until rice is a little drier.

title: mexicali chicken 'n cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, 1 cup cheese, corn and soup.
Spread into pan.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix well; put in loaf pan and place in icebox until hard. Slice when ready to eat.
Put remaining in refrigerator.

title: rich baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in oleo and shortening.
Add liquid to dry ingredients, stirring just to mix.
Roll out on floured surface to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Especially good for shortcake.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in milk.
Continue stirring until boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Add white baking chocolate and vanilla, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Pour into bowl and cool.
Whip the cream.
Add powdered sugar.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl layer:

title: gringo dip
directions: Salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Serve with corn chips.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges.
Mix with nuts, pineapple and sugar.
Pour into container and let chill.
(Soften Jell-O in boiling water.)

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place about 2 tablespoons chicken mix on wide end of each triangle; roll up.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour half of soup mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square baking dish.
(Reserve remaining sauce.)
Arrange filled crescents over soup mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons cheese on top.
Return to oven 5 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted. Serve with remaining sauce.

title: bacon bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and put in large bowl.
Saute onions and green peppers in margarine.
Add bacon bits and cheese.
Stir into bowl with quartered biscuits.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan (lightly greased) for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 1 greased and floured cookie sheet or 2 (9 x 12-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: "leftover turkey" soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, combine turkey, water, bouillon, salt, poultry seasoning and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, then stir in barley.
Re-cover. Simmer 30 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Stir in carrots, onion and celery.
Simmer uncovered an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables and barley are tender.
Then stir in parsley last.
Makes 8 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan. Mix German chocolate cake as directed on box. Pour into pan.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Break cauliflower in buds and boil in salted water for 15 minutes.
Save 1 cup liquid and drain rest.
In chicken broth, cook onion, carrot and seasonings.
Add flour to melted butter. Add water and half and half to broth.
Bring to boil.
Add cauliflower, pepper and butter/flour mixture.
Simmer to warm.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.

title: tuna-swiss pie
directions: Pierce pastry thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes.
Remove.
In a large bowl, toss together next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into pastry.
In bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Slowly pour over tuna mixture.
(It may be too much liquid, so just use the amount necessary to cover the mixture.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, depending on one's oven.
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.
Serves 8.
Freezes well.
Reheat slowly, covered.
Uncover for last 10 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms and onion in margarine.
In small bowl, mix soup, milk and Miracle Whip. Spray 2 quart casserole dish with non-stick cooking spray.

title: bakery frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients for 5 minutes until light and fluffy. Makes enough to frost one 2-layer cake.

title: log roll cake
directions: Line large cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Mix cake as directed.
Pour and spread evenly on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Let cool at least 6 hours.
Must be very cool for cake to roll without breaking.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce in strips and fill bowl 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Layer celery, peppers and onions.
Layer peas on top.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and layer on top.
Add cheese.
Add bacon.
Needs 8 hours to chill.

title: snack cereal mix
directions: In large bowl, mix cereal and oyster crackers together. Measure 1/3 cup popcorn oil.
Pour over top of dry cereal and crackers, gently mixing well to coat all.
Sprinkle dry party dip mix over cereal mixture.
Mix well to coat.
Gets better as it sits a while.
Store in airtight container.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
In baking dish, mix soup, rice (raw) and orange juice together.
Lay browned pork chops on top.
Bake 45 minutes, covered, 15 minutes, uncovered, at 400°.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Cook to boiling.
Cool and put in freezer.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix well.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons potato flakes and 1 cup warm water the next day.
Let it stand at room temperature. To make bread, take out 1 cup and feed with the same ingredients as listed.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to jell. Fold in pineapple and carrots.
Return to refrigerator until fully jelled.
Cut into squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: fresh broccoli salad(takes 20 minutes to make.)
directions: Place in a large bowl the following:
Cut broccoli tops into bite size pieces; finely chop tomatoes and onions.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper for taste.
Mix again.
Allow salad to chill for approximately 1/2 hour in the refrigerator. This will allow the juices from the tomatoes to mix up with the mayonnaise.
Mix again and serve.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread on muffin halves and cut halves into quarters.
Broil for 7 minutes or freeze and broil when needed.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak into strips; sprinkle with paprika.
Fry steak and garlic in butter until brown.
Add peppers and onions; cook until soft.
Add tomatoes and broth; cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Blend water, cornstarch and soy sauce; stir into steak. Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Cream together in mixing bowl the margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and milk.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff; gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold egg white mixture into first mixture. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish, buttered.
Set dish in shallow pan containing boiling water 1-inch deep.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool.
Serve cold with or without whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual in the 2 cups of water.
Boil chicken until it comes off bone easily; save the broth.
Place rice in bottom of large baking dish (2 quarts or more).
Add chicken (off bone) on top of rice.
Pour both cans of soup over chicken; add onion and 1 cup of broth.
Place sliced cheese on top, then cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in 6-quart pot covered with water.
Put in 4 bouillon cubes and parsley.
When chicken is tender, take out of pot.
Cool, then debone.
Set aside.
Now put broken up dumplings in water that chicken was taken from and 1 package Lipton chicken noodle soup mix.
Put chicken back in pot.
Turn stove down low and cook this until dumplings are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir mixture slowly into cooked rice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add raisins if desired.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Preheat oven to 300°. In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour; blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out onto a wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Combine with undiluted soup.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine ingredients; blend together with fork.
Let stand in a refrigerator in a covered container for 1 to 2 weeks before using. Makes about 4 cups.

title: peach salad
directions: Heat Jell-O, sugar and pineapple to boiling to dissolve sugar. Let cool.
Add buttermilk; stir.
Add Cool Whip and stir well. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes about 3 cups. Can be drained rom meat for a second use.
Can also be frozen.

title: wild rice fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Use skillet or deep fryer.
Have oil very hot.
Use funnel. Hold funnel over oil and move in circular motion and then crisscross motion as you pour the batter through the funnel into the oil.
After cake is a light golden brown, drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: roseanne's shipboard curry rice and chicken
directions: After cooking rice, add the Dijon mustard, honey and curry; mix.
Then add canned chicken or chicken which has warmed to room temperature to this mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend together condensed milk and egg yolks.
Gradually beat in lime juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into milk mixture.
Pour this mixture into graham cracker crust and smooth out the filling.
Whip the whipping cream until very stiff and add a dash of sugar when half-whipped.
When stiffly beaten, smooth on top of pie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain well.
Combine cheese, soup, mayonnaise and onions in casserole dish.
Add broccoli to mixture, then crumble Ritz crackers until all of dish is covered; pour melted butter over crackers and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crackers are browned.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain. Add soups, sauce and evaporated milk.
Heat until thickened.
Line a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Pour half the meat mixture on.
Add another layer of tortilla shells.
Pour remaining meat mixture over shells. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: valerie's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directions call for.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except dressings.
First, add the regular Italian dressing.
Mix and refrigerate.
One hour before serving, pour and mix creamy Italian dressing.

title: country style cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Grease skillet or pan; place in oven to heat. Combine ingredients in order listed; blend well. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Makes one 9-inch skillet or one 9-inch square pan.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Melt chocolate; combine dry ingredients.
Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, then add chocolate, egg and vanilla, beating well.
Add flour mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix orange juice, honey and dressing; pour over wings.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is golden brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch pan, then sour cream over beans, then layer with tomatoes, then layer with onions, olives and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: tabbouleh(lebanese salad)
directions: Cover bulgur with cold water and let soak for about 30 minutes. Test a few grains to see if they are soft but still slightly chewy. Drain off excess water.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Beat all together; fry in oil like pancakes.
Serve with brown gravy.

title: barbecued beef and beans
directions: In a crock-pot, combine kidney, pinto and white beans with onion.
Top with beef cubes.
Do not mix.
Combine the barbecue sauce, ketchup and brown sugar.
Pour 1 cup sauce mixture over all. Do not mix.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 hours.
Remove cover.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Cook, uncovered, 1/2 to 1 hour longer.
Serve over split French rolls, in pita bread or over noodles or rice.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows first. Add rest of ingredients; mix well.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Pinch up cake in small pieces.
Cut up cream cheese into small pieces.
Whip milk and Dream Whip together.
Add powdered sugar into the Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese into the Dream Whip and powdered sugar mixture.
Put half of cake into pan; then pour half of whipped mixture onto cake, then rest of the cake and then the rest of the whipped mixture.
Then add cherries on top.
Chill before serving.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Rinse potatoes in water; do not pat dry.
Turn slices in sugar to coat both sides.
Repeat.
Coat each with flour.
Cook half of potatoes in 2 tablespoons butter over medium-low heat for 10 minutes each side.
Remove and keep warm in 300° oven.
Wipe out skillet and repeat procedure with rest of potatoes.

title: missouri muddies
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pan.
Add sugar, milk and cocoa. Bring to a boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Quickly stir in peanut butter and oats. Quickly drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: mom's "rhubarb cream pie"
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Add to rest of rhubarb, etc.
Pour in pie crust.
Brush top crust with a little milk and sprinkle sugar on it.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat with mixer until smooth.
Add taco sauce.
Spread in bottom of 8-inch dish.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple yam puff
directions: Drain and discard 1 cup syrup from pineapple.
Beat yams with remaining ingredients until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until puffed and lightly browned.
Serve with pork or poultry.
A good Thanksgiving dish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda well.
Pour in cooking oil and vinegar.
Pour water over all.
Stir; do not beat.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes or test with toothpick.

title: fruit balls
directions: Combine pecans, dates, cherries, pineapple and vanilla in a large bowl. Sift flour, sugar and salt together and blend with the mixture. Fold in egg whites.
Form into small balls. Bake at 325° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Makes about 11 dozen.

title: orange icicle cake
directions: Mix all together and put in two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut layers in half. Frost between layers and around layers.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup slowly and stir often until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Pour over popcorn slowly and stir well until coated.
Spread into ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Turn often with pancake turner.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Ready to eat.
Store in airtight container.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Use stone crock. Put boiling water over flowers and let stand 1 1/2 days. Strain, add sugars and juices.
Wait 24 hours, then add yeast cake. When scum rises add egg white.
Wait 3 full days, strain.

title: vegetable cheese chicken soup
directions: Heat broth, add potatoes, carrots and onion; cook 15 minutes. Add other ingredients.
Stir and heat until well blended.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar, egg yolks and flour; then add to milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from fire; add butter, coconut and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until meringue is browned.
Yields 1 pie.

title: st. joseph's succo
directions: Add olive oil to heavy stock pot and saute onions until transparent.
Add
anchovies
and
saute
until
melted.
Add tomato
paste, puree, salt, sugar, pepper, oregano and crushed garlic
plus
sweet basil and saute well.
This takes approximately
minutes,
stirring constantly.
Then add water and fennel
greens and simmer 3 hours.
This recipe doubled serves approximately 50 people, making a large electric roaster full. Add additional water as needed.

title: jalapeno-pineapple coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sour cream, jalapenos, mustard, sugar, lemon juice, and salt.
Add the cabbage and pineapple and stir well.
Cover the slaw and refrigerate it for at least
1 hour.
Can be prepared up to 1 day ahead.
Stir in the green onions and adjust the seasoning just before serving.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook
grits in boiling water about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add cheese and
garlic powder.
Cook until cheese is melted.	Add water for thinner grits.
Serves 4 or more.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: nutty noodle crunch
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Heat butter and honey to boiling.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over noodles. Toss to coat evenly.
Spread in a 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Loosen from pan. Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix well and put in baking dish. Put in oven at 350° until mixture is hot and bubbling (about 20 to 30 minutes). Eat with your favorite crackers or chips. Delicious!

title: 24 hour kosher pickles
directions: Boil water and kosher salt together for 2 to 3 minutes.
When stops boiling, add vinegar.
In large jar, put pickling spice, dill and garlic.
Fill jar with pickling cucumbers (sliced longways).
Pour liquid over pickles, etc.
Close cover.
Leave out until cool.
Refrigerate and use next day.
They keep well in refrigerator.

title: fisherman's potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place potatoes in rows (overlapping a little) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: pink punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves, then cool.
Combine juices, sugar and water and chill.

title: round up chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in water 2-inches above the beans. Simmer beans in same water until tender, 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Saute pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender, but not browned.
Remove vegetables and set aside.
Add parsley.

title: easy corn bread
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
together (cornmeal, salt, baking powder,
soda
and	flour).
Just
when ready to bake, add the liquids
(egg,
buttermilk	and cooking oil).
Stir only until dry ingredients
are
mixed
with
liquids; pour into greased muffin pans
baking pan (10 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches). Bake approximately 20 minutes less for muffin pans.
Should be golden brown when done.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach in small amount of water with minced onion until thawed.
Beat eggs, sour cream or milk, Parmesan cheese, flour, butter and salt and pepper with spinach and onion.
Bake in a greased round casserole for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set in a 350° oven.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add wafer crumbs, alternating with milk.
Add coconut, pecans and raisins.
Bake in oblong pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
While hot, poke holes with fork.
Pour hot icing over cake.

title: french toast
directions: Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper in a shallow bowl, beating well.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet.
Dip 2 bread slices, one at a time, into egg mixture, coating well.
Drain. Arrange in skillet and cook over medium heat, 4 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Remove to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, beaten eggs, crackers, margarine and grated onion. Fold in 1 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake as directed. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. In a bowl, mix Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Spoon over top of unbaked cake. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; let cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars together.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Fold in oats, pecans and raisins.
Be careful not to add too many oats.
Cookies will be dry.
Bake at 350°
on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes just until edges are brown.
Makes about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, syrup, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar with mixer. Blend well and spoon into graham cracker crust; refrigerate.
Eat plain or add your favorite topping.

title: good seasons fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well, leaving skins on the potatoes.
Slice potatoes thin.
Slice onions thin.
Place in
a large skillet and cover with half of Italian dressing liquid.
Cook on medium heat and keep pan covered.
Turn frequently until crispy brown.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: rhubarb conserve
directions: Put ingredients in a large pan and let set overnight.
Put on stove; cook slowly, stirring often until cooked.
Put 1/2 cup walnuts in 10 minutes before sealing in jars.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Add milk to right consistency.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: hearty pressure cooker soup
directions: On waxed paper, coat meat with flour.

In heated 4-quart pressure cooker, without rack, in hot butter or margarine, brown meat well. Add carrots, celery, onions, potatoes, cocktail vegetable juice and 2 cups hot water or enough to make cooker 2/3 full. Add salt and seasoned pepper. Bring pressure up on cooker. Cook 15 minutes. Remove from heat and reduce pressure quickly before uncovering.
Makes about 11 cups or 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake with penuche frosting
directions: Combine oats and water. Let stand while mixing rest of cake. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Using electric mixer, cream brown sugar and margarine in large bowl. Add eggs and beat well. Stir in dry ingredients, then vanilla, oats mixture and nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 9 inch pan or 7 x 11 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes. Cool and frost with Penuche Frosting.

title: stuffed minute steak
directions: Mix honey and soy sauce; set aside.
Combine hot water and butter or oleo in a bowl; stir in stuffing mix and green pepper. Put on steak and roll up.
Put honey and soy sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients.
Add 5 tablespoons of salt and enough cold water to cover and let stand overnight.
Rinse in cold water 3 times and drain, then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, coconut and pineapple.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together Crisco, salt and brown sugar.
Add eggs, milk, syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes or until knife comes clean when tested in center of pie.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until liquid.
Pour over other ingredients and mix well.
Pack in loaf pan.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; mix well.
Then add flour and soda alternately with the buttermilk; mix well.
Beat egg whites stiff. Fold in batter and cream together.
Fold in coconut and nuts. Bake in layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry onion in butter in a heavy pan over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, corn, water, salt and celery salt.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are done.
Add milk, cream and pepper.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in roaster, flat side.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Combine ingredients and heat to a boiling.
Pour over ribs and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg until foamy.
Beat in brown sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to first mixture.
Mix in pecan pieces.
Spread in well sprayed baking pans.
Bake until top has dull crust.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Cool, then remove from pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken tuna casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add flour; blend.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Garnish with almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dijon potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: chicken salad in cantaloupe rings
directions: In medium bowl combine oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Blend well.
Add chicken; stir grapes, mandarin orange segments, pineapple and rice mixture.
Blend well.
Add chicken mixture to rice mixture; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Cut cantaloupe crosswise into 1/2-inch thick rings. Remove seeds and rind.
Place cantaloupe rings on lettuce-lined serving plates.
To serve, stir almonds into chicken salad.
Spoon into center of each ring.

title: tupperware bread
directions: Place flour
in
Fix
and
Mix
Bowl.
Make
"well"
in center.
Mix milk, water, eggs, sugar, salt and yeast in Mix N Store or mixing bowl.
Beat one minute!
Pour into flour well. Do not
stir!!!
Seal,
burp
bowl and wait until seal breaks. Now add
melted
butter
and mix.
Add more flour if necessary until dough
is
not
sticky.
Seal,
burp and wait until seal pops off again.
Now
divide into 3 loaves.
Knead on lightly floured pastry
sheet.
Put into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool and enjoy.

title: powdered cocoa brownies
directions: Combine
sugar
and
Nestle
Quik
(thoroughly).
Add successively oleo, pecans,
vanilla
and
lightly beaten eggs. In separate bowl, combine
flour,
salt
and
baking
powder. Combine all the above and
mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake
pan and bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes.
Dip
top
of
each brownie in powdered sugar and place on
cake
rack to cool.
After cooling, brownies may be stored in freezer to keep them moist.

title: sugarless fruit bars
directions: Combine dates, prunes and raisins in hot water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in softened margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix into date mixture and add nuts.
Spread into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: herb green beans
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Toss gently.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently until heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: florentine crescents
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine spinach, process cheese spread, crumbs and bacon.
Stir over low heat until cheese spread is melted.
Unroll dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each half lengthwise, forming 32 triangles.
Spread each triangle with rounded teaspoonful spinach mixture.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush dough with beaten egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: goop
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and coloring.
Pour into trays or into a tub.
Observe and explore.
No finished product, just exploration. Keep reusing mixture (can be stored in a tight container).

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all but oranges in saucepan.
Boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve in warm mug with orange slice.
Serves 8.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add juice from pineapple. Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy and fold in pineapple, cottage cheese and remaining ingredients.
Place in any size pan or jello mold of your choice.
Chill until firm.

title: apple cranberry salad
directions: Put in an 8 or 9-inch square dish.

title: applebrosia
directions: Mix orange juice with water.
Peel and grate apples, putting immediately into orange juice and water mixture.
Add crushed pineapple and coconut (optional).
Chill covered.
Add sliced bananas immediately before serving.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
