title: chocolate satin frosting
directions: Blend sugar and hot water into chocolate.
Beat half of egg into chocolate mixture, then beat in remaining egg.
Beat in butter or margarine, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Blend in extract.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon fat in 10-inch skillet.
Add cabbage.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until light brown.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in whipping cream and lemon juice; heat until cream is hot. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: scents of christmas
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer. Add additional water when needed.
Store in the refrigerator, covered, for several days and reuse as desired.

title: spareribs(my style)
directions: Warm pan up.
Steam spareribs in a pan for 1/2 hour (turn them).
Throw out water.
Add ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Cook about 1/2 hour, then add lemon slices; cook 3 minutes longer.
If you see it's too thick, add more ketchup and water.
Add no oil, the spareribs have plenty of grease in them (good flavor).
Enjoy.
Serve with white rice or as a side dish.

title: old south chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
When chicken is very tender, remove from stock, reserving the stock.
Cool, then take meat off the bones.
Cut chicken meat into bite size pieces.
In a skillet, melt the margarine.
Add the flour, salt and pepper; stir.
Slowly add the chicken stock, stirring to keep mixture smooth, then add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken and chopped eggs; mix well.

title: pizza
directions: Cook pepper, onion and celery in saucepan until tender. Prepare pizza crust according to package directions.
Place in pizza pan and place in oven.
Cook until hard but not completely done.
Take out of oven and spread ground beef over crust.
Top with onion, pepper and celery mixture.
Spread sauce from pizza mix over the vegetables.
Next, sprinkle the cheese from mix over the sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven to finish cooking.
Take out when Mozzarella cheese is golden brown.
Use temperature given on package.

title: mexican dip
directions: In large pan, pour tomatoes.
Slice chunks of cheese and add to tomatoes.
Melt the cheese.
Add ground beef.
Heat well. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and water on stove (at simmer setting) until water is absorbed.
Combine all other ingredients with rice and put in buttered casserole.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Mix or stir casserole after first 30 minutes.

title: jon yougel(a dutch cookie)
directions: Let butter stand until soft.
Cream well with sugar.
Add egg yolk and mix well.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add cinnamon. Knead.
Pat down on cookie sheet.
Brush with unbeaten egg white to which has been added a little water.
Sprinkle with a little sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: peanut chip fudge
directions: Melt chips
and
milk
in a double boiler.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Spread in wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan. Cover.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut.

title: quick frankfurter dinner
directions: Brown franks; remove to side dish.
Pour off fat.
Cook celery and onion in chicken broth until liquid is gone.
Add everything else; cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter together and start cooking.
Stir constantly over slow heat.
After it reaches a rolling boil, cook 2 more minutes.
Take from stove and add Hershey bars, chocolate drops and Marshmallow Creme.
Add pecans.
Pour into buttered pan. Cut into squares when completely firm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine eggs and oil in a medium mixing bowl; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to oil mixture, along with buttermilk.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well. Pour batter into a well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until the center is firm.
Cut into squares.

title: pineapple burgers
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Divide meat into 4 thin patties.
Place a ring between two patties, sealing edges.
Place burgers on rack 6 inches from broiler.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.
Pour Spicy Sauce over burgers; serve at once.
Serves 2.

title: clams casino
directions: *Place clams in the freezer for 12 minutes.
This will allow easier opening.
Open with appropriate clam knife.
Clam knife will split clam into 2 even portions per clam.
Place each 1/2 clam on a cookie sheet to wait for the sauteed mixture.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix flour, quick oats, brown sugar and oleo until crumbly. Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tarasawa's chow fun
directions: Brown pork and drain excess fat.

Add water chestnuts, garlic, ginger root and oyster sauce. Cook on low heat 20 minutes. Prepare egg noodles according to package directions. While egg noodles are cooking, add onions and bean sprouts to pork and let cook over low heat for 10 minutes, covered. Add egg noodles and soy sauce to pork mixture and toss. Serves 8.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Make into balls or drop by teaspoonfuls.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: In order given, add each ingredient, mixing after each.
Place in muffin tins.
Sprinkle mixture of ground cinnamon and sugar on top of each.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium to large casserole dish, mix green beans, mushroom soup, milk, pepper, mushrooms and 1/2 of the dried French onions.
Mix well.
Use the rest of the dried onions to sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook hamburger until done, drain.
Put in large pan or crock-pot.
Add diced tomatoes and chilies, the special sauce with tomato bits, onions, celery and green peppers.
Add American cheese.
Stir often until cheese is melted.
Dip with tortilla, nacho or Dorito chips.

title: no name cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in crispy rice, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Roll into balls and flatten or just drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; form into 18 meat balls.
Brown in oil and drain.

title: kentucky fruit pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with a mixer, then stir in all the rest with a spoon.
Put into pie crust and keep in refrigerator overnight or at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mashed turnips
directions: Peel and cut turnips into small dice.
Place in saucepan with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low flame until very tender.
Remove from heat and mash until smooth.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, Pet milk, water and margarine in heavy saucepan.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat.
Add pumpkin, vanilla and spices.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mom's best caramels
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and 1 pint of cream; heat to 230°.
Add 1 pint of cream; heat again to 230°.
Add 1 pint of cream again and heat to 240°.
Remove from heat.
Add paraffin wax and vanilla. Stir until wax is melted.
Pour in a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Cool.
Cut and wrap in wax paper.

title: mandarin chicken dinner
directions: Using an electric skillet, heat oil slightly.
Add chicken and cook for 3 minutes.
Mix Miracle Whip with orange juice and brown sugar, then add to chicken and stir.
Add green pepper.

title: caesar's salad
directions: Wash lettuce and tear into large pieces.
In salad bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, mustard and pepper.
Add egg yolk* and mix well.
Add lettuce, croutons and Parmesan cheese and toss lightly.
Sprinkle each serving with additional cheese.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix and pour into 6 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: mama's potato soup
directions: Mix onions and celery in pan; cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine and milk to taste.

title: honey chicken
directions: Using large skillet, saute onions in margarine.
Place flour, salt, pepper and paprika in paper bag.
Add chicken and coat thoroughly.
Lay floured chicken in skillet on top of onions and brown slightly.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add wet.
Add nuts and cherries last.
Garnish top of cake with additional cherries and pecan halves if desired.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done (test with a toothpick).

title: 3 day potato salad
directions: Layer in the following order two times: potatoes, onion, cottage cheese, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and Accent. Refrigerate for 3 days before eating.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and dry caps.
Mix all ingredients, except onion rings.
Stuff caps, mounding slightly.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Heat slightly.

title: pecan goodies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Dip pecans in mixture and lay on cookie sheet, not touching each other.
Heat in oven at 250° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 cup liquid from asparagus into cream of mushroom soup. Arrange half of asparagus, cheese, eggs and crumbs in alternate layers in buttered casserole; sprinkle with seasonings.
Repeat layers.
Pour the mushroom soup mixture over this and garnish with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onion, garlic and oregano.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Arrange alternate layers of cooked noodles, grated cheeses and meat sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella slices.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before cutting.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: blue plate beef patties
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg.
Stir in onions, bread crumbs and mustard.
Add beef.
Mix well.
Shape into patties.
In an ungreased skillet, cook patties.
Drain.
In a small bowl, combine gravy, water and horseradish.
Add mushrooms.
Pour over patties. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: sauteed zucchini and tomato
directions: In a skillet, heat dressing over medium heat.
Add zucchini and add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes with juice and basil.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend well, eggs, oil and sugar.
Add zucchini and vanilla, then dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quick 7-up strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up until thick.
Add red food coloring.
Slice strawberries in a baked pie crust.
Pour mixture over berries and cool.
Cover with whipped topping.

title: sander's hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy pan or top of double boiler.
Over low heat, stir and blend until all ingredients are melted, about 15 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Pour into jar; cover and refrigerate.
Will be stiff when cold.
Warm before using.
Great over ice cream.

title: raspberry custard brulee
directions: Gently rinse raspberries and divide evenly among 4 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Set aside.

title: sunshine salad or dessert
directions: Combine pie filling, milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Fold in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cut biscuits into 1/4; arrange on top. Bake 20 minutes more.

title: white french salad dressing
directions: Shake well in a large screw-top jar or salad dressing jar. Refrigerate and remove garlic clove before serving.
Delicious on any green salad, especially a spinach, fresh mushrooms and thinly sliced Vidalia onion salad with crunchy bacon bits sprinkled on top.

title: congo bars
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix together with eggs and sugar.
Add butter and mix.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil very slowly until soft. Add tomato sauce, basil, salt and pepper.

Cook slowly until noodles are cooked, Ricotta filling is ready and vegetables are cooked. When all 4 groups are ready, put in layers, starting with just enough sauce to wet the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add layer of noodles, cheese, kale, carrots and layer of noodles. Pour remaining sauce on top.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain on paper towels until all water is out. Mix all ingredients together and leave in refrigerator one hour or until vegetables are soft.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Crumble half bag of corn chips and spread on bottom of pan. Mix chicken, Ro-Tel and soups together.
Spread mixture over corn chips.
Add rest of corn chips and sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: snappy french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Cover and process at "mix" until blended.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: egg souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt together.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist peanut butter cookies
directions: *For a drier cookie, omit caramel.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill before serving.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice together.
Add Cool Whip and
rest of ingredients together; stir mixture good.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
These pies freeze good.

title: chilled gazpacho with a crisp basil leaf
directions: Chop all the vegetables to an even size, around 1/2 inch dice. Place the ingredients in a tray and leave in the refrigerator over night.
Blend in a food processor, but make sure it is still chunky.
Line a plate with clingfilm.
Lightly coat the basil leaves with olive oil and lay flat on the clingfilmed plate. Microwave at full power for 20 seconds.
Allow to rest and repeat. If the leaves are large it may be necessary to repeat the process. Spoon soup into bowls and garnish with the basil leaf.
Serve chilled.

title: pineapple orange squares
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter; stir in the flour, coconut and brown sugar.
Press mixture into bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool. Stir ice cream to soften.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and orange juice concentrate until fluffy.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls; beat smooth, stir in pineapple.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Freeze 8 hours or overnight.

title: oven-fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in shallow dish; set aside.
Dip tomato slices in water; dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray; spray each slice of tomato.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes more or until golden.
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, broth and water in saucepan.
Simmer, covered, 35 minutes.
Pour into blender.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan and heat to boiling.
Stir in milk. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; garnish with chives, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add softened orange sherbet. Refrigerate until almost set.
Add drained crushed pineapple, drained mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served.

title: easy sweet-sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in a shallow baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves with water.
Pour over chicken and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco potato shells
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cut in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
(Refrigerate pulp for another use.)
Brush inside and outside of potato skin with butter.
Place cut side up on a baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut cake 3
directions: Mix coconut milk and Pet milk.
Pour over cake.
Top with whipped topping.
Spread coconut on top.

title: skillet dinner for 2
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown pork chops on both sides; sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Peel sweet potatoes; slice thin. Add margarine and melt.
Add sweet potatoes, turning once.
Cook until nearly done.
Peel and slice apples in eighths.
Set pork chops aside.
Add apples, brown sugar and salt over apples and potatoes.
Cover skillet and cook on low until tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients, cook 1 hour in hot oven in dry cast iron skillet.

title: mama ethel's hot water cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, salt, flour and baking powder. Add water until you can stir but not soupy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill ingredients overnight and mix the day you want to serve.

title: bleu cheese salad dressing
directions: Combine oil, mustard, salt and sugar in the container of a blender.
Blend on high for a few seconds.
Add onion, vinegar, egg, garlic, Parmesan, oregano and celery salt and blend again. Stir in Bleu cheese.
Pour into a jar with a cover and refrigerate.
Keeps about 2 weeks.

title: raspberry-beet gelatin mold
directions: Boil the beet juice, water and sugar with cloves for 5 minutes. Pour over dry jello through a sieve to drain off cloves.
Mix until crystals melt.
Cool about 20 minutes in refrigerator.
Add vinegar and beets.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve with a mix of Miracle Whip, horseradish sauce and Cool Whip to taste.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8. Can do ahead.
Has to set.

title: ham noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Saute green pepper in butter or margarine.
Add gravy.
Add ham.
Put into a 1-quart casserole. Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Serves 4.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Saute onion and bay leaf in butter until onion is tender and golden.
Remove bay leaf and discard.
Add flour to onion and butter; cook and stir for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Return to heat and bring just to boil.
Let simmer gently and add pureed cauliflower.
Add cream to hot soup.
If too thick, you may add milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon tea cookies
directions: Pour vinegar into milk.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat egg and lemon peel.
Alternate milk-vinegar and sifted flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Drop on cookie sheet by 1 teaspoon of dough.
Bake at 250° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: vegetable batter
directions: Beat the egg, and add enough water to make a medium batter, after adding all the other ingredients.
Dip any of your favorite vegetables in the batter and fry in oil.

title: raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Place all ingredients into a large jar.
Shake well.
Chill and serve over salads.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Mix baking soda, baking powder and cream of tartar into flour. Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 425° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg yolks with 1 cup sugar.
Add the cocoa, baking powder and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add vanilla and salt.
Fold the cocoa mixture into the beaten egg whites and pour into a well-greased 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour batter over pecans and coconut.
Heat butter and cream cheese until soft. Beat in powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over cake mix.
Smooth over top with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mash berries.
Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve over hot water.
Add berries and juice that have been sweetened with about 1 cup of sugar.
Combine the creams; whip.
Add berries and test sweetness.
Turn into freezer tray; beat when partially frozen. Return to tray; freeze.
Serves 8.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients well except potatoes and cheese and put meat mixture into medium size loaf tin.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cook 45 minutes or to your likeness.
Remove from oven and cover with mashed potatoes and then sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Return to oven to reheat and melt the cheese.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over medium heat to full boil (exactly 3 minutes).
Remove.
Stir in oats, cocoa and vanilla. Beat until it begins to thicken.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 11 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Cook in oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in a blender or food processor; set aside. Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Blend together creamed mixture and pudding mixture.
Place lid from whipped topping tub in the bottom of an 8-inch plastic flowerpot to prevent leaks.
Place a layer of crushed cookies in the flowerpot and top with a layer of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers and top with a final layer of cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.
Decorate with silk flowers, plastic plant or real flowers and serve with a new enameled trowel.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and roll.

title: carrot cake
directions: Add first 8 ingredients as listed; beat for 8 minutes, then add carrots, nuts and raisins.
Mix and bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
When cake is placed in oven, put shallow pan of water on rack under cake.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Butter a Bundt pan.
Put cherries in bottom of pan.
Place the rolls in a circle on top of the cherries.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour melted butter over rolls, then sprinkle on dry ingredients.
Cover with greased foil.
Set on counter to rise. Bake the next morning for approximately 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on plate to serve.
Be sure to remove foil to bake rolls.
These smell and taste divine!

title: mid-season apricot jam
directions: In a large saucepan cover apricots with water.
Boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain water; then add pineapple, sugar, orange juice and salt.
Stir until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook, uncovered, until mixture thickens (stir often to prevent scorching) about 30 to 40 minutes, depending on size of open pan. Add almonds and place in jars to cool.
Store in refrigerator. Recipe makes 3 1/2 to 4 pints.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Put hamburger and remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low about 3 hours.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl combine first five ingredients and set aside. In a small bowl combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice. Beat with rotary beater 1 to 2 minutes to blend well.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Serve on lettuce cups.
Serves 10.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Grate sweet potatoes (have 3 cups).
Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, salt, spices and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and beat thoroughly. Add milk.
Melt butter and pour into greased casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until golden brown.
Grated orange rind or raisins may be added before baking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 c. pecans.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Chill thoroughly.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice meat diagonally across the grain with a very sharp knife into 1/4-inch thick strips 4-inches long (set aside).
Combine remaining ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour the marinade mix over the beef strips in a shallow glass dish. Marinate for 30 minutes, turning the meat several times.
Arrange beef on cake racks placed on cookie sheets lined with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven at 180° for 12 hours.
Remove the jerky from the racks.
Cool to room temperature before storing in airtight jars.

title: savory chicken roll-ups
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water until done; I add celery, onion and carrot for seasoning.
Debone chicken and cut into small pieces or grind in food processor until coarse.
Let broth stand until congealed in refrigerator.
Scoop off fat.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix ingredients!
Bake 1 hour at 300° in baking dish.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender except carrots, onion and green pepper.
Pour liquid over vegetables and refrigerate.
Stir before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and stir into eggs.
Add milk and pumpkin.
Fill pastry shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 35 minutes longer or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beet salad
directions: Dice all ingredients, add sugar, salt, pepper and mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill; serve cold.

title: ponyarotti's
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt with yeast mixture and water to make dough workable.
Take tablespoon of dough and make a round flat surface.
On half of round put 1 teaspoon ground beef, 1 teaspoon cheese and 1 teaspoon Ragu; fold over and seal.
Drop in hot grease until brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter and olive oil in skillet.
Add all seasonings and cook until clear.
Put in white and claw crab meat.
Salt to taste and add 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper.
Put in bread crumbs.
If dry, you can add more butter or olive oil.
When cool, add beaten eggs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add all ingredients, except bread crumbs, together.
Place in large baking dish; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Cook rice; drain.
Mix broccoli and rice.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Add mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Put cake mix, butter and egg in bowl and cut with knife until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar together and pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: party mix
directions: Mix light brown sugar, margarine and Karo syrup.
Put in boiler and bring to a boil.
Slow boil for 5 minutes.
Do not stir.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla and soda.

title: cardamon cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; knead until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake 2 inches apart on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and syrup until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Pour on buttered pan.
Let set until firm before cutting into squares.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Place shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs in a mixing bowl; beat.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in oats.

title: party meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, cornflake crumbs, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and minced onion; blend well.
Form into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Arrange in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
In saucepan combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Cook over moderate heat.
Stir occasionally until mixture is smooth and cranberry sauce is melted.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine and cut with pastry blender flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Then add the oatmeal.
Mix together and put over sliced apples which have been sprinkled with cinnamon.
I also sprinkle water over this, usually about 1/2 to 2/3 cup depending on whether or not you like a chewy topping (without the water, it will be a more crumbly topping).
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
You can check doneness by inserting a fork into apple slices.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until creamy.
Layer in bowl chunks of cake, cream cheese mixture, fruit and glaze. Repeat; will make 2 layers.
Let sit overnight.
Other fresh fruits may be used such as peaches and pineapple with peach glaze.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together, except croutons or stuffing.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in oven, uncovered, until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.
Put stuffing on top at beginning of cooking.
Bake at 350°.
Serve hot.
This recipe may be cut in half.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems from mushrooms. Grate the stems in a food processor. Save the caps.
Melt butter in a skillet. Add onion, pepperoni, garlic and stems. Cook until tender.
Add cracker crumbs, cheese and seasonings. Spoon into mushroom caps. Fill a glass baking dish with caps.
Add 1/4-inch water on the bottom of the pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: male cookies(because females like them)
directions: Using a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, place brown sugar and butter in pan and bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
As the mixture cools, add one egg at a time and stir well.
Sift the flour and measure 1 cup.
To the flour, add salt and baking powder.
Stir into mixture and mix well.
Add pecans and stir.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, spray with Pam or Baker's Joy. Pour mixture in pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
After cool, cut into squares.

title: ground beef pot roast
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in center of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Slice the following 1/4-inch thick: 3 potatoes, 3 carrots and onions.
Place around meat.
Mix and sprinkle over meat: 2 teaspoons parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into long glass 13 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: chocolate cake surprise
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add chopped onion and rice to oil.
Stir until the rice is light brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Turn down heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat and let sit 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix yogurt, salad dressing mix and onions in small bowl. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, stir in milk until well blended.
Makes about 2 cups.
Has 25 calories per serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Spread meat in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour pizza sauce over meat.
Add your favorite toppings.
Sprinkle 2 cups Mozzarella cheese over the last topping.
Mix the biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Pour over the top and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix in order given and freeze for 24 hours.
May use bowl or 9-inch square container.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Cook together in a sauce pan over low heat the half and half, whipping cream, beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir constantly until the mixture reaches a temperature of 160 degrees.
At this temperature the mixture will lightly coat a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and add the milk to make 1 gallon.
Chill the custard base completely before freezing in the ice-cream maker.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop pepper, onions, celery, olives and pimentos.
Combine with mayonnaise and mix with pasta and chill.

title: holiday beef tenderloin
directions: Remove beef from refrigerator 1 hour before roasting.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place beef in foil-lined pan.
Combine oil and salt, brush over beef.
Rub all over with garlic and pepper.
Roast 35 to 40 minutes (meat thermometer 130° for medium rare).
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes or up to 2 hours before slicing.
Slice beef. Arrange on platter.
Serve warm or at room temperature with horseradish sauce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the beans and corn (drain well).
Spread evenly in casserole dish.
Mix the sour cream, celery soup, minced onions and cheese.
Spread evenly over beans and corn.
Crush crackers and cover evenly.
Melt butter and spoon over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle French fried onions on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes, or until onions brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together until fluffy the sugar and eggs. Add oil.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Add carrots, raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake 2 round pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cooled, cut cake in half.
Break cake into small pieces and line bottom of a large glass bowl. Pour 1/2 of the Kahlua over cake mixture.
Next, pour on 1 box of prepared instant pudding and then 1 container of Cool Whip on top of that.
Repeat for a layer effect.
Refrigerate overnight if possible.

title: cranberry candy
directions: Melt cranberry sauce over low heat.
Add gelatin and sugar. Bring to boil on low heat.
Add walnuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm. Cut into squares and roll in granulated sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: aunt ease's oatmeal coffee cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and butter.
Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: double-chocolate pecan balls
directions: *Do not add the ingredients called for on the label directions.

title: easy onion soup
directions: Cook onions in olive oil until golden brown.
Sprinkle flour over onions and brown flour.
Add water all at once.
Stir well to avoid clumping.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Liberal is better.) Allow to cook down for a bit for thicker soup.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Pour into pie shell.

title: spanish beans
directions: Let beans soak overnight. Put in fresh water. Add salt. Chop onion and pepper. Add to beans with a can of diced tomatoes (or canned tomatoes). Let cook for several hours on a low temperature.

title: honey butter bar
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pack in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch
pan.
Beat
other 3 ingredients 3 to 5 minutes and layer over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
May be soft in middle when taken out of oven.

title: dolly's pie crust
directions: Crumble flour, shortening, sugar and salt together.
Add water, vinegar and egg.
Roll out and shape as desired.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes enough crust for 2 double crust pies.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend oil or melted butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs; using a spoon, beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from the edge of pan.
Cool.
This recipe can be doubled for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion soup mix, milk and egg.
Make loaf.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon onto loaf.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, add juice to all ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Refrigerate or serve warm.

title: quick cobbler cake
directions: Spread peach pie filling into greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Spread margarine evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until brown on top.
Leave in pan.
Cut and serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
Any other fruit pie filling can be used.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden brown. Add tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add water, carrots, celery, potatoes and green beans.
Continue cooking until tender.
Add zucchini, cabbage, peas and pasta during last 15 minutes.
For added flavor, stir in 1 or 2 tablespoons pesto sauce.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Place frozen chopped broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cooked cut-up chicken.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Top casserole with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients of Miracle Whip, vinegar and milk. Pour over broccoli, onion and cheese.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and press in bottom of pan.

title: nine day pickles
directions: Cover whole cloves with boiling water; allow to stand overnight.
Drain and repeat this procedure for 3 days.
On 5th day drain and slice to 1/2-inch chunks.
Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar.
Bring to boiling point and pour over cukes. Let stand 2 days.
On 3rd day, bring to boil, put in hot sterile jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: kim's chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except for flour and milk.
Put in casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Combine flour and milk; pour over top of chicken mixture and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening with egg. Add sifted dry ingredients with mashed bananas. Add rolled oats and chocolate chips. Drop on cookie sheet, a teaspoon at a time, and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: hasty cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and place in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour onto melted margarine.
Don't stir.
Pour fruit with juice or pie filling onto batter.
Don't stir.
Bake at 375°
for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: marinated onions
directions: Mix other ingredients and pour over thinly sliced onions.
Put in glass jar.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will last for several weeks.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Crumble cheese and sausage together with fork.
Work into flour mix and add water.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 75.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and salt onto waxpaper.
Combine water, shortening and butter in medium saucepan; heat until fats are melted.
Pour into large bowl; stir in molasses.
Add flour mixture, 1/3 at a time, blending well to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl; chill several hours, or until firm enough to roll.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until firm at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken and corn casserole
directions: Melt the margarine in skillet; add flour.
Blend well and stir over low heat until bubbly.
Add broth, all at once, stirring constantly until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper; combine corn, chicken and sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs blended with 6 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crumbs are brown and sauce is bubbling at edge.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Add beaten eggs and bananas which have been well mashed to creamed mixture.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt. Add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (or larger if you wish).
Bake for 25 minutes or when the cake springs back to touch of finger.
Cover with 7 Minute Frosting or frosting of your choice.

title: kolaczki cookies
directions: Cut cheese and shortening in flour as for pie crust.
Form into ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bring to room temperature and roll out thinly.
Cut in circles or squares.
If circles, put finger indentation in middle and put in filling.
If square, place filling in middle, lift opposite sides together and pinch.
Bake on cookie sheet, lightly greased at 350° for about 15 to 25 minutes, depending on size.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: one dish meat loaf
directions: Mix ground round, salt, pepper, soup, onion, oatmeal and egg. Spray casserole or loaf pan.
Slice potatoes thin and lay on bottom of casserole dish.
Place ground beef on top.
Mix brown sugar, catsup and dry mustard.
Spread on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain grease.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake sweet potatoes in microwave, cool and then peel.
Put in mixer bowl and add white sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well; then pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ham and swiss quiche
directions: Grease or spray quiche dish with Pam.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in dish.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 400° oven or until golden brown and knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients; mix well.
Roll teaspoonful into ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 1 inch apart.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Place in brown bag and shake with powdered sugar.
Great for kids to shake and bake!!

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift flour.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Blend in sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Fold in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Mix topping together and crumble on top of mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Add marshmallows and brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 300° oven until firm.

title: cranberry bread pudding(with orange sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In large bowl, combine bread and milk. Set aside. In medium bowl, combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, and orange rind.

Mix until blended. Pour the egg mixture into the bread/milk mixture. Mix well. Stir in cranberries and pecans. Melt butter in 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Pour pudding into pan. Bake 1 hour. Serve with warm orange sauce.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: self-rising yeast rolls
directions: Combine over heat the shortening, milk, hot water and sugar until sugar dissolves. Cool. Add dissolved yeast and blend well. Add flour and mix thoroughly in a greased bowl. Lightly grease top and cover with waxed paper and terry towel. Let rise until double in bulk; work down, kneading dough until smooth on floured board. Roll or cut as desired. Let rise and bake at 400° to 450°. This dough can rise overnight or stored for 1 week in the refrigerator.

title: cottage cheese rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Sift flour, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt together in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add yeast, cottage cheese and eggs, mixing well.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon salt and remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Spread over dough. Roll as for jelly roll and slice.
Place in greased baking pan. Let rise for 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, sugar and oil together.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder; add to egg mixture.
Beat well. Fold in persimmon and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and lightly floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean when tested.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: clara's whole wheat biscuits
directions: *Gradually add more buttermilk if dough is too stiff.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix half of flour mixture with the sugar and oil mixture, then add the other half of flour mixture with 1 egg at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cajun biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Toast seed and butter together at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix seed with cheese, paprika and garlic powder. Roll biscuits in mix and bake as any other bread.

title: paprika cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into logs. Roll in paprika and chill. Serve sliced on Ritz or your favorite crackers.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Add vanilla, water and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Run all vegetables through food chopper and soak in salt water a few hours or overnight.
Drain and mix well.
Bring to a boil in vinegar and spices (do not cook).
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: cocktail pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 or 4 layers.
Spread each biscuit round with the mixture and place on a pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake now or freeze for later.
Place in plastic bags until ready to use.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: delicious salad dressing
directions: Mix oil, salt, sugar and vinegar together, then beat in catsup and finally, add sour cream, beating it in gradually.
This is a delicious dressing for fish, vegetables, tomato or hearts of lettuce salad, and is equally good used as a sauce for shrimp. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: carne con salsa tomate
directions: Chop onion and cilantro very fine.
Brown ground beef and add salt, pepper, garlic and onion.
Add tomato sauce and cilantro and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with white rice and black beans or mashed potatoes.

title: dianne's pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and pecans.
Mix to coat pecans.
Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and add pecan mixture.
Bake at 300 to 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes not to let the pecans get too brown.
Remove from pan and place on foil to cool.

title: bacon almond dip
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
In food processor with metal blade or in mixing bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream, chili sauce, hot pepper sauce and pepper (freshly ground) to taste.
Add scallions, bacon and almonds and process or mix until blended but still chunky.
Remove to bowl and refrigerate until ready.
May be refrigerated for 2 days.
It also may be frozen; defrost in refrigerator.
If dip is too thick, stir in additional sour cream.
Makes 2 cups.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add melted German chocolate and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Put in a greased and floured 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Check for doneness.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruits and set aside.
Combine Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in bowl and chill.

title: apple scallop
directions: Combine apples, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice in large bowl.
Toss lightly to mix. Mix flour and brown sugar in a medium size bowl with pastry cutter until crumbly.
Spoon half of apple mixture into an 8 cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with half each of the raisins and crumb mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, pecans, syrup, vanilla, salt and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: white nut fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer or until a little mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir; add flavoring.
Beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss (about 8 minutes).
Stir in the candied cherries and walnuts and quickly pour into greased (with butter) shallow pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: olivia's aunt sharon's chewy cakes
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle pecans over mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: dunkers delight
directions: All all ingredients on top of mayonnaise in blender.
Blend.

title: 4 bean plus red and green(easy and quick salad)
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli, onion and bouillon cube in casserole dish. Cover with water and microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Mix broccoli with soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add yellow rice.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Place on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large skillet, cook chopped celery and chopped onion until tender and they appear transparent.
Add chicken broth and cream of mushroom soup.
Add grated cheese, sliced olives, broken pecans and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cut up chicken and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve on chow mein noodles or rice.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add mushrooms, onions and garlic. Cook until mushrooms and their liquid cooks away.
Add meat, breaking lumps with spoon.
When meat is brown, add tomato sauce, broth and seasoning and sprinkle flour over surface.
Mix well. Allow to simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove skillet from heat; add sour cream.
Cook noodles until almost, but not quite, done.

title: peanut and corn flake candy
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and syrup.
Bring to rolling boil.
Boil for approximately 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Pour onto greased pan.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: sunday night soup
directions: Chop onion coarsely and fry in pan until golden.
Add hamburg and brown lightly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat and simmer all together for about 2 hours.
Best when made ahead and reheated.

title: lemon-chicken pasta
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil. Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Add peas and carrots; saute 1 minute.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Add broth and cream cheese to skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat 3 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring constantly with a whisk.
Stir in chicken mixture, pasta and next 4 ingredients.
Cook 1 minute.
Garnish with chives, if desired. Yields 2 servings.

title: new england clam chowder(south of boston-style)
directions: Wash clams thoroughly.
Place them in a deep pan with the cold water covering the clams.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes or until shells open.
Strain the broth through cheesecloth (or strainer) and reserve.
Remove clams from shells, clean and chop. Combine salt pork and onion in saucepan and cook gently over low heat, about 3 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add broth and potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add clams.
Remove from heat and slowly add milk and cream which have been heated.
Serve immediately!

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat chops with mix as directed on package.
In 13 x 9 pan, place single layer.
Toss onions with oil; place over chops.
Bake 30 minutes or until cooked through. Pour gravy over chops; cover.
Bake another 15 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in pureed strawberries and ReaLemon.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust (mixture should mound slightly).
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: hot cranberry citrus punch
directions: In large
kettle combine ingredients except ginger ale. Simmer over medium
heat about 15 minutes.
Remove spices just before serving.
Add
ginger ale and heat through.
Serve hot, if desired garnish with additional cinnamon sticks.

title: saucy hot dogs
directions: Make sauce by sauteing onions in butter until tender.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer about 2 minutes.
Place wieners in baking dish and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: greek salad
directions: Clean all vegetables.
Slice cucumber into round slices and tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Slice onion in half, the slices into single moon slices.
Separate each slice.
Cut olives into slices.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate until 1 hour before serving.
Add Feta cheese.
Cut into small bite size pieces; add low calorie dressing.
Mix well and garnish with chopped green onions.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: 1-2-3 bread
directions: Beat the mixture about 17 times by hand.
Mix and put in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or longer, if needed).

title: stromboli
directions: Prepare favorite bread recipe.
Roll out to 1/4-inch rectangle.
Across middle horizontally, place a single layer of ham with a single layer of cheese on top.
Fold over from bottom. Repeat ham and cheese layers on top of dough that is covering first layer.
Fold over from top.
Seal all edges.
Poke holes in top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and slice.

title: peachy almond muffins
directions: Chop peaches and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and make a well in the center.
Add eggs and oil; stir until moistened.
Add peaches and remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes for 6 jumbo, 20 to 25 minutes for 12 regular, or 18 minutes for 36 miniature muffins.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and green peppers; mix with 1/2 cup of salt.
Cover with ice cubes or cold water.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours, until cucumbers are crisp and cold.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Remove tips from chicken wings; break and separate again at joints.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken in baking dish.
Marinate 1 hour.
Pour juice off.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no cook fondant
directions: Blend butter, syrup, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Add sugar, all at once.
Mix together.
Knead with hands.
Turn onto board and continue kneading until well blended and smooth. Store in dry place.

title: strawberry-kiwi pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip to pudding mix.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding and fruit twice and finish with rest of Cool Whip.

title: cream ball
directions: Mix ingredients together; form ball and roll in the walnuts. Refrigerate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Have all
ingredients
at room temperature and measured in advance.
Butter
an
11 x 16-inch piece of foil.
Spray a quart size
microwave dish with Pam (I use Vision Ware with a handle). Cook sugar and syrup on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in margarine, vanilla
and
peanuts
with a wooden spoon sprayed with
Pam. Cook
more
minutes;
stir in soda with sprayed spoon.
Pour immediately
onto
foil
and spread quickly with sprayed spatula. Cool completely and break up.
This is easy, but you must have everything ready and work fast.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Place celery, onion and broccoli in a saucepan with water; cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Set aside.
Blend cottage cheese in blender or food processor until very smooth. Slowly add milk while continuing to blend; add chicken soup to cooked undrained vegetables.
Heat through without boiling.
Add salt and pepper.

title: oven fried fish(for people who like fried fish)
directions: Rub fish fillets with
half a lemon and soy sauce, then coat with
olive
oil.
Mix breadcrumbs, salt, pepper, garlic powder, paprika and dry mustard.
Cover fillets liberally with mixture. Bake in a 350° oven until the fish flakes.

title: dilly potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water and cook until tender. Drain and cool.
In small bowl mix remaining ingredients pour over cooled potatoes and toss to coat.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese into bowl; combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Form into two balls.
Roll each ball in pecans and garnish with sliced green olives, if desired.
Refrigerate until firm, then slice.

title: chocolate cake log
directions: Add salt to eggs; beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, vanilla and pancake mix.
Stir lightly until batter is smooth.
Spread batter evenly in greased, wax paper lined jelly roll pan (10 x 15 x 1-inch).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 7 x 11-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Cook together dates, prunes and raisins in water.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
When melted, stir until well blended. Add beaten eggs and vanilla; beat until blended.
Mix all dry ingredients in separate bowl while cooking raisins, prunes and dates.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Spread mixture in prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together all ingredients until mixed well.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving with potato chips or crackers.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Use to marinate beef, pork or chicken.
Makes 2 1/3 cups.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in serving bowl, except the following:

title: chicken a la maria
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken breasts first in flour, then in egg wash, then in bread crumbs.
Place on the bottom of a high sided greased glass dish (13 x 9-inch).
Set remaining mixture aside.

title: potato salad
directions: For the dressing, boil above ingredients (except the potatoes) in a saucepan.
Cook 10 potatoes.
Cut warm potatoes through a coarse grater.
While potatoes are still warm, mix in hot dressing.
When salad is cold, add chopped celery, onion and boiled eggs.

title: a quick cookie
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Roll in small balls.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry cake mix, 3/4 cup margarine and 3/4 cup nuts.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Mix brown sugar and cream cheese.
Spread evenly over the bottom mixture.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until edges are brown.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: hot garlic potato soup
directions: In a soup pot, melt butter and saute onion and garlic until onion wilts.
Add red pepper flakes and saute 1 more minute.
Add the potatoes, celery, cabbage and chicken broth.
Simmer for 15 minutes (vegetables will be crispy tender, if you prefer, cook longer).
Remove 2 cups of the cooked vegetables.
Combine with milk, flour and sour cream, then puree in a blender or food processor.
Stir the mixture into pot with other vegetables.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat until hot but "not" boiling.
Enjoy!

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and yogurt.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt and add to first mixture.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts; sprinkle over top and swirl into batter.
Cover pan with waxed paper and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Add cream of chicken and cream of celery soups.
Add water and mixed vegetables (optional).
Mix altogether.
Place deboned chicken on top of the mixture.
Add salt and pepper.

title: cherry whip
directions: Quick and easy-dump all ingredients in large bowl and mix. Pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and chill.
Great for family and friends gatherings.
Use as dessert or side dish.

title: u.m.w.'s apple and date pudding for "ten"
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let stand.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg and blend.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla, then add apples, nuts and dates from which liquid has been drained.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with Brown Sugar Sauce.
Serves 10.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine and pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour into pan. Drain fruit if canned and combine with water and sugar.
Carefully pour into pan.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 1 hour.
When done, the batter will have risen to the top and should be a beautiful brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Cook in saucepan or skillet until light colored (just before it spins a thread).
Cool slightly.
Pour over cake.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix rest in bowl for 5 minutes.
Grease and flour tube pan. Put 1/3 batter in pan. Put half of apples on top of half of sugar and cinnamon mixture. Pour rest of batter, apples and mixture.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: grilled salmon with fresh dill sauce
directions: Season the salmon with a generous sprinkling of lemon pepper seasoning.
Place on grill and cook until tender. I use the George Forman grill and it usually takes about 4 minutes. The amount of time can vary due to the thickness of the salmon.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust according to directions on package for 2 crust pie.

title: treet stew
directions: Cut up potatoes and onion in a three-quart pan.
Mix potatoes and onion in pan with water and bring to a boil.
Cut heat down to medium and add meat, salt, pepper and ketchup.
Let cook on medium heat for about 1 hour.
Check every 15 minutes to see if stew is done.
Stew will be done when potatoes are cooked well.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
In a large bowl, add shrimp, peas and cucumber (take inside seeds out of cucumber).
Mix milk and salad dressing until creamy.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together (a little of each). Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: italian cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 large or 3 small pans.
Pour batter into greased pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 package poultry stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut (pecan) brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until mixture strikes a boil.
Then add peanuts (or pecans).
Cook to hard-crack stage (295°).
Remove from stove and add soda; stir.
Pour on buttered cookie pan and spread.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Chill dough in fridge until firm (overnight).
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate with colored sugars.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not let them turn brown.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Mix together the margarine, flour and milk.
Batter will be thin.
Pour this batter over chicken and bake at 375° until bubbly and top crust is brown.

title: slice and bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt, stir well; set aside.
Combine sugar and shortening, cream well, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Divide dough in half, shape each half into a 12 x 12-inch roll.
Wrap in waxed paper, and chill overnight.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices, place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together and drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer. Serve soup and top with cheese, Fritos, sour cream, lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: creamy peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches and 1/2 cup sugar; mix well and let stand 5 minutes.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Stir first six ingredients into a medium bowl.
Using an electric beater, beat butter, sugar and honey in a large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients. Combine. Gather dough into ball. Divide into three pieces, flattening each into circles.
Wrap in plastic and chill until firm (3 hours).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook whole chicken until falls away from bone, then remove chicken from broth and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan, laying chicken on bottom of pan only.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat with a fork until all cake mix is absorbed.
Press into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma mcmillen's fudge
directions: Mix and boil sugar, cocoa, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball stage.
Cool mixture for approximately 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat with a spoon until ready to set. (The fudge will lose its glossy look.)
Pour into a small greased pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Scald milk and cream on medium heat.
Thoroughly mix flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add dry ingredients to milk.
Mix until thick.
Let boil slowly for a couple of minutes.
Beat the egg yolks.
Gradually add pudding mixture to yolks, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute on low.
Take off heat.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with meringue, if desired.

title: seven layer overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass or Tupperware dish (only use glass or Tupperware).
Cover with mayonnaise and sugar, then layer of grated cheese.
Top with crumbled bacon. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
(May use Bac*Os instead of bacon.)

title: french toast
directions: In a bowl scramble eggs.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well. In a frypan melt a little butter.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Butter and sprinkle generous amount of powdered sugar on toast and serve immediately.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown. Add chicken broth and zucchini.
Simmer until tender.
Blend (in blender) small batches of zucchini and broth until smooth.
Add half and half or milk as you blend.
Season to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: bala parmesan chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir well and set aside.
Combine cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Dip in egg mixture, then in flour mixture. Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave oven for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time and beat well.
Add flour.
Beat in extract and 7-Up. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pat out cookie dough to 10-inch circle on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes, until golden brown. Cool.
(To speed cooling, place in freezer for 2 minutes.)

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat by hand.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven; pour on marshmallows and return to 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: million dollar fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and allow to set in a cool place until it thickens.
Makes a large amount.
Will serve several.

title: bacon-potato frittata
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until browned.
Remove to paper towels to drain.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons bacon drippings from skillet.
Heat drippings until hot.
Add potatoes.
Cover skillet and cook until tender and lightly browned on both sides, turning potatoes occasionally, about 15 minutes.

title: squash muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake at 350° until done.

title: tasty ham loaf
directions: Hollow loaf; mix ingredients.
Put in hollow loaf.
Put top on loaf and wrap in foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thready. Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat and add butter, soda and salt; stir fast and pour onto buttered foil.
Set.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: ricotta egg biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, Ricotta cheese and flavoring; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, gradually.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, blend sour cream and egg.
In medium bowl, mix breadcrumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken in sour cream mixture, then roll in crumbs.
Place in oiled shallow pan and bake until tender (45 minutes).

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes the day before and refrigerate.
Next day, grate coarsely and mix with other ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Add corn and cheese to meats until melted.
In separate bowl mix cornbread mix, buttermilk and eggs.
Add to first mixture. Pour into 9 x 14-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Use a large bowl and layer the first 7 ingredients as listed. Spread mayonnaise over top, evenly, to cover entire top.
Spread sugar evenly over the mayonnaise.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, cut the boiled eggs and place evenly over top.
Sprinkle bacon bits across top. Sprinkle grated cheese liberally across top.

title: meat loaf with sauce
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Shape
into
loaf and put in a deep dish.	Mix
remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf. Bake at 350° one hour or until done.

title: bavarian meatballs and pears
directions: Drain pears, reserving syrup.
Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, egg, milk, salt, pepper and allspice.
Mix well and shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown meat balls slowly in oil.
Add reserved pear syrup, vinegar, brown sugar, pickling spice, cloves and dried apricots (if you have them).
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add pear halves and simmer 15 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put sugar and corn syrup in boiler on medium heat.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in baking powder and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; put in oven for 15 minutes at 300°.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: pecan cake
directions: Mix pecans with 1/4 cup flour and set aside.
Cream butter and Crisco slowly adding sugar.
After creaming butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time, beaten well after each egg.
Add sifted flour and soda, along with buttermilk.
Blend well and stir in pecans and mix.
Add flavoring. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and put Cream Cheese Icing on cake.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix egg and 1/3 cup catsup in a large bowl.
Stir in bread crumbs; then mix in meat until blended.
Pat half the meat over bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with layer of spinach, then cheese.
Pat remaining meat on top.
Spread with remaining catsup.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix nuts, dates, flour, sugar and other ingredients with the eggs.
Mix well.
Spread 2 small loaf pans with Pam and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes two (1-pound) loaves.

title: homemade cookie mix
directions: In a 6-quart or larger bowl, cream shortening and sugar with an electric mixer, adding sugar to the shortening gradually. Thoroughly blend remaining ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture slowly using low speed on an electric mixer or a pastry blender to mix until like coarse cornmeal.
Store in tightly covered containers at room temperature.
Cookie mix will keep several weeks.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix and pour over cooled cheesecake when you are ready to serve.

title: crustless ricotta pie
directions: Beat cheese and
sugar, then alternate, adding eggs and flour. Add
remaining
ingredients.
Fill greased and floured pans to slightly below
top
(pies
puff
up,
then
sink when cooled). Sprinkle tops with cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and roll into walnut-size balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Serve warm.
May be frozen before baking.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute the onion, celery and green pepper in the oil until just tender.
Add the meat and cook until it loses its color.
Add the chili powder and tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat. Stir in the rice and salt; warm through.
Place contents in a baking dish in layers alternating mixture and cheese.
Sprinkle cheese over top and place in microwave long enough to melt the cheese.

title: roasted tomato bruschetta
directions: In large roasting pan, combine tomatoes, garlic, Essence, olive oil and salt. Toss gently and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until slightly browned. Serve on toasted French bread, sprinkle with basil leaves, cheese and additional olive oil, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and jello to a boil.
Let cool until syrupy (not firm).
Mix cheese, sugar, baby food and Cool Whip.
Add to pineapple mixture and let set.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix together.
Freeze in gallon containers.
Thaw 4 1/2 hours before using.
Add 1 bottle unchilled ginger ale.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding in fruit juice until thick and glossy.
Cool. Mix the pineapple and mandarin oranges with the pudding and add any or all of the fresh fruits.
This makes a large salad and keeps well in the refrigerator for several days.

title: butter baked chicken and gravy
directions: Dip chicken in canned milk, then roll in flour, salt and pepper mix.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Put floured chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake uncovered in hot oven, 400° to 425°, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over; pour mixture of soup, water and milk over and around chicken.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut orange slices (use hot knife and put a little powdered sugar to keep from sticking).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemon butter chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Melt margarine and add lemon juice.
Brush chicken with lemon butter.
Crush Rice Krispies with rolling pin and sprinkle over chicken.
Pour remaining lemon butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fried green tomatoes parmesan
directions: Lightly sprinkle tomatoes with salt; drain on paper towels a few minutes.

title: shrimp on rice
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in melted butter in large saucepan. Add celery soup and milk.
Blend well.
Add shrimp and last 4 ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
This is good served on rice with a salad and corn sticks.

title: holiday bells
directions: Mix ham, cream cheese, Worcestershire and cayenne in small bowl.
Stir in chopped peppers.
Cover and refrigerate 60 minutes. Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chicken-sour cream casserole
directions: Combine chicken broth, sour cream and soup.
Combine melted oleo with cracker crumbs.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into casserole dish. Cover with chicken and pour broth mixture over chicken.
Top with rest of cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swanson chicken casserole
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish and place onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: casserole for hungry people
directions: In large casserole (depending on the size of the meal wanted) arrange one layer of each of the following in order: sliced raw potatoes (sliced thin for quicker cooking), sliced onions, cut up celery (including leaves), sliced American cheese, 1 pound wieners (cut in 1/4-inch slices) and 1 can soup mixed with 1/2 soup can of milk.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until potatoes are done in a 350° oven.

title: potato meat loaf
directions: Peel and grate potatoes; rinse and drain. In a large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, egg, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add ground beef and mix well. Pat meat mixture into an 8 1/2 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until no pink remains; drain. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Pat 1/2 mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool and add filling.

title: buffalo wings hot sauce(an authentic recipe)
directions: Melt butter in a pan, add hot sauce and vinegar.
Pour hot sauce mixture over chicken wings and mix well to coat.

title: mama's toasted oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand.
Mix all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal, mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian salad
