directions: Toss the above ingredients and sprinkle with Salad Delight. Refrigerate.
Serves approximately 10.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips and margarine with sweetened condensed milk; remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill 2 hours or until firm. Remove from pan.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt oleo and pour over graham crackers.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside to cool.
Beat eggs, oleo and powdered sugar for 10 minutes and pour over top of graham cracker crust. Top with bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight and garnish with nuts and maraschino cherries on top.

title: veal scaloppine with tomatoes and olives
directions: Coat both slices of veal (or chicken) with egg, flour and egg. Heat 2 tablespoons oil and 1 tablespoon of butter in skillet. Cook over high heat 1 minute each side.
Transfer to warm platter. Add remaining 6 tablespoons butter.
Add pepper (red or green) to taste.
Cook, tossing and stirring until peppers are crisp-tender. Add tomatoes and cook 1 minute.
Add oregano and vinegar and cook over high heat about 1 minute.
Pour mixture over veal and sprinkle with parsley.

title: magic puffs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip marshmallow into melted margarine; roll in sugar-cinnamon mix. Wrap a crescent triangle around each, completely covering marshmallow.
Dip in margarine again.
Place in muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix the margarine, sugar and milk in a large pan on top of stove.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 10 minutes, then remove. Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until everything is dissolved.
Pour onto a large, buttered cookie sheet and cool.
Slice into squares.

title: spinach lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles according to package directions. While the noodles are cooking, saute the onion and garlic in the olive oil, adding a tablespoon or two of water as needed to keep from sticking.
Combine the Ricotta, Parmesan, spinach, egg whites, black pepper, parsley and sauteed onion and garlic, mixing well.
Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread 1/4 of the tomato or spaghetti sauce over the bottom and then arrange a layer of noodles.
Top with 1/3 of the Ricotta-spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of the Mozzarella and top with tomato sauce.
Repeat layers twice more, ending with sauce.
Cover pan with aluminum foil, crimping edges tightly. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Makes 12 servings.

title: stay in bed stew
directions: Place all ingredients into large casserole (9 x 13-inch) dish. Cover with aluminum foil and bake 5 hours at 275°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: vegetable-cheese soup
directions: Heat vegetables, beer and instant bouillon to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except parsley.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients; stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, cream of coconut, both milks, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs and coat well. Add coconut and pecans; mix well.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spritskabucken
directions: Using electric mixer, cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, yolks and walnut meats.
Gradually add flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Refrigerate dough for at least 4 hours.
Using cookie press, make figure 8 shaped cookies approx. 1-inch long.
Bake at 350 degrees 7 minutes each shelf.
Finish cookies will be slightly brown on edges and very crisp when cool.
Traditionally these cookies are made 2-3 months in advance so they have time to become stale and become crisp again.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix together in a large saucepan the brown sugar, 1 cup water, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, salt and nutmeg.
Cook until boiling is reached.
Add cranberry sauce; beat until smooth.
Add the water and pineapple juice.
Dot with butter.
Serve with cinnamon sticks.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all together and put in baked pie shells.
Refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: miss faye's pecan pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, pecans and add syrup, vanilla and eggs, mix well.
Pour into un-baked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: new england roast
directions: Sear the roast in the shortening in a skillet.
Brown it good on all sides.
In a pot, big enough to hold the roast, mix all the ingredients except the water and flour.
Make sure roast is almost covered.
Double the recipe if not.
Simmer on low heat and slow for several hours.
(I usually do mine overnight.)
Remove roast and drain onions from liquid.
Make gravy with liquid, water and flour.
(Use cornstarch if you'd rather.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and layer in casserole dish.
Combine Cheez Whiz and celery soup in saucepan.
Pour mix over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: steak diane
directions: Place slices of filet on a flat surface.
Pound with a flat mallet to about 1/4-inches thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil and 2 tablespoons of butter in large skillet.
When very hot, add steaks.
Cook about 1 1/2 minutes on one side; turn and cook about 30 seconds on the other side. Transfer to hot serving dish.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vinegar, vanilla and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll very thin.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 48.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add sherbet last. Serve.

title: roasted chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 550°.
Clean and dry chickens inside and out. Rub each chicken outside with cross-cut garlic clove; repeat inside, leaving garlic clove in cavity.
Season inside and out with salt.
Squeeze juice of one lemon inside and out.
Sprinkle liberally with rosemary.
Season, again inside and out with salt and pepper.
Put chickens on rack in pan in oven and reduce heat to 400°.
Roast 1 hour and 10 minutes without opening door.
Drain juices from cavities into pan.
Set chickens aside to cool, then refrigerate.
Remove rack from pan and stir in a few drops of vermouth.
Place over high heat and cook a few minutes, scraping bits from bottom and sides of pan.
Refrigerate pan juices several hours or overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and set aside.
Combine cornmeal, eggs, milk, sugar, oil, creamed corn, pepper and grated onion.
Pour half of mixture into greased iron skillet.
Then spread cooked hamburger meat over mixture.

title: ham and belgian endives
directions: Blanch endives in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
Let cool. Roll each endive in a slice of ham.
Arrange side by side in an oblong, buttered baking dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Makes 2 regular size loaves.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with hand mixer.
Chill and serve with chips or vegetables.

title: tomato bouillon
directions: Boil until soft; strain.
Reheat and add salt and pepper. Seal hot.
To serve, add sugar to taste.
Blend with flour and butter.

title: hummus
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor with a steel blade and process until hummus is coarsely pureed. Taste for seasoning and serve chilled or at room temperature with pita chips or pita bread.

title: snappy red salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Serve with baked tortilla chips.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 cups.

title: hearty oatmeal
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the milk, oats, salt, raisins and apples.

Bring the oatmeal to a boil, reduce the heat, cover the pan and simmer the cereal, stirring it often, for about 5 minutes. Add the sunflower seeds and cook the oatmeal for another 5 minutes or until it reaches the desired consistency.
Serve the oatmeal sprinkled with cinnamon-sugar, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Put a layer of meat mixture in a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Layer cheese and tortillas, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Stir ingredients well and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda into mixing bowl. Form a well in your dry ingredients and add melted shortening, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in lightly greased and floured 9 inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven 350° for 30 min.

title: beef stew
directions: *Chop and mash with salt, or spear with toothpick, or use powdered or granulated garlic.

title: mulled wine
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a Dutch oven over medium heat; bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer 5 min.
Add wine; simmer 10 min.
Pour mixture through a wire-mesh strainer into a container; discard solids.
Garnish, if desired.
Suggest using a Burgundy wine.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Begin with Crisco, sugar and egg.
Add all other ingredients together and mix well.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: oriental dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Chill covered. Makes about 2 cups.

title: biscuits(serving size: 20)
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Put corn oil in measuring cup and fill remainder of cup with buttermilk and stir.
Pour milk and oil into flour and stir with a spoon.
You may have to add a small amount of milk or flour to make the mixture the right consistency to place on a cutting board.
Pat the mixture to about 1/2-inch thick and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Spray biscuit pan with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Note:
Yields about 20 biscuits, 2-inches wide.

title: pineapple orange congealed salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and applesauce. Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Spoon applesauce mixture over fruit.

title: chili cheese corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Blend chili powder with lemon juice; mix other ingredients. Chill. Serve over any seafood; shrimp, oysters, crab meat, scallops, etc.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and eggs in top of double boiler and cook 20 minutes over boiling water.
Do not stir.
Cool.
Add to cooled mixture the self-rising flour, nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter in pan with melted butter and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cover as soon as you take out of oven. Let cool to cut.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Combine mashed potatoes with milk, salt, pepper, onion, butter and egg yolks.
Mix well.

title: pan pierogies
directions: Melt oleo and saute onions.
Cook potatoes and mash like you would mash potatoes (but keep firm).
Add American cheese and stir until melted.
Stir well.
Put some oleo and onions in bottom cake pan.
Lay lasagna noodles on top of oleo, then add potato mixture. Put oleo and onions over potatoes and put lasagna noodle on top of potatoes and pour the rest of oleo and onions.
Cover with tinfoil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until noodles are soft.

title: crisp cereal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar (white and brown).
Add beaten eggs and vanilla and mix until smooth.
Add flour with soda, salt and baking powder added and mix well.
Add cold cereal, rolled oats and coconut and mix thoroughly.
The dough will be crumbly.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press slightly.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate icing
directions: Mix in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil rapidly for 7 minutes. Remove from heat and cool a little. Beat until of spreading consistency and creamy.
Will frost sheet cake or 3 or 4 layers.

title: lazy man's stew
directions: Dice meat into fairly good size cubes and place in a large ovensafe dish.
Add tomato soup and water.
Peel and cut up tomatoes, carrots and onion.
Add to meat and soup.
Add bay leaf and peas.
Salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and cook at 250° for 5 hours.

title: sauteed squash
directions: Wash and slice squash, removing seeds, if desired.
As water accumulates, add onion and bouillon cubes.
Saute until tender.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix jello and boiling water until dissolved, add cold water. Let sit until slightly thickened.
Mix pineapple, bananas and marshmallows with the jello.
Let sit until thick.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg until thick then add cream cheese and let cool.
Spread on jello mixture and top with Cool Whip.
You can also add coconut and nuts, if desired.
Yields a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Then add nuts and strawberries.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in 8 wedges.
Arrange potatoes with peel side down in 2 shallow baking pans.
Mix ingredients together and brush oil over the potatoes.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or microwave on High for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add shortening, egg, milk and corn.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon into hot fat. The grandkids loved these with ketchup.

title: chili burger
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer for 35 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken 'n chilies casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine sour cream, light cream, onion, chilies, salt and pepper; stir in potatoes, chicken and 2 cups of the cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Also, cooked turkey and ham can be substituted for the chicken.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix together and serve with pretzel sticks.

title: y. p. s. spaghetti sauce(to serve 100)
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Drain well. Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Pour into glasses and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and chill.

title: bacon tastees
directions: Cut bacon slices in half. Wrap bacon around each cracker. Bake at 350° until bacon is done.
Cool.

title: powdered sugar replacement
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor. Process until well blended and powdered. Transfer to airtight container. Yield: 4 cups.

title: refrigerator bran muffins(makes 18)
directions: Pour boiling water over bran cereal; mix and let cool before adding buttermilk.
Cream together sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir cooked bran mixture into creamed sugar and shortening.
Add dry ingredients all at once; stir just until moistened (batter will not be smooth).
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight or until needed.
Can be stored up to three days.
Bake in oven at 425° in muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in microwave (use paper cups) for 45 seconds on High.
Bake in toaster oven at 425° for 20 minutes (use foil cups).

title: tim's banana bran bread
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Measure the bran, mashed bananas, shortening and sugar into a bowl.
Add the water and stir until well mixed.
Add the egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to the banana mixture, stirring only until combined.
Bake in greased custard cups or well-greased bread pan, 45 minutes.

title: snickers apple salad
directions: Combine sour cream and Cool Whip.
Stir in Snickers and apples.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Use as basting sauce for chicken, spareribs, hamburgers and hot dogs.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; pour into a bowl.
Sprinkle with dry orange Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cold pack pickles
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients well.
Add cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Cover and seal.
Refrigerate.
Will keep all winter.

title: chicago-style pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and stir well.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients (flour, salt and 1 teaspoon sugar).
Add oil, second 1/2 cup water and yeast mixture.
Mix to form dough; knead 3 to 5 minutes.
Let rise in a covered bowl until doubled (1 1/2 hours).
Spread on a 14-inch pizza pan (greased).
Preheat oven to 475°.
Prick dough all over and bake 4 minutes.

title: pumpkin eater pumpcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin tins with paper liners. Combine cake mix, pumpkin, water and eggs.
Mix as directed on cake package.
Stir in chips.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: coconut pecan chess pie
directions: Bake crust at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs well; stir in sugar, milk, oleo, lemon peel and peel, flour, cornmeal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Pour into crust and make tent over pie and bake for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: farmer's country breakfast
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook sausage over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned.
Remove sausage from pan, leaving drippings.
Add potatoes and onion to drippings.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally until potatoes begin to brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and parsley until blended.
Pour over potato mixture.
Add reserved sausage.
Scramble.
Top with Cheddar cheese, cover and heat until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: mary's yellow cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs and beat well.
Beating thoroughly makes cake light.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour mixture; add vanilla.
Pour into 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: island baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In boiling water (enough to cover), simmer shrimp with cayenne, 5 minutes.
Drain and dice.
Arrange in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine mustard, sugar, steak sauce, butter, Texas Pete and salt.
Pour over shrimp.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until crumbs are golden.

title: peanut butter fluff candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar to soft ball stage, stirring constantly, as it burns real easy.
Stir in chunky peanut butter and the Marshmallow Fluff.
Pour onto a buttered cookie pan, cool and cut. Very good.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into an 8, 9 or 10-inch square or 7 x 11-inch rectangle pan.
Bake about 45 minutes until set.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: canned chow chow
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients into large container (consistency of slaw).
Pour 1/2 cup salt over and let set overnight.
Drain, then put in enough vinegar to cover.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 box pickling spice.
Let come to boil for 5 minutes and pack in jars.
Water bath can for 30 minutes.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Place in buttered casserole.
Place layers of potatoes, onions, ground beef and green pepper.
Pour soup, bouillon, Worcestershire, salt and pepper over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Boil kielbasa for 10 minutes and drain.
Cut into bite size chunks and mix with sweet and sour sauce and pineapple (the juice too).
Heat through and serve.
Great for backyard picnics and barbecues!!

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix together very evenly with your hands.
Smash evenly all the way to the edges of a jelly roll pan, pressing very firmly. Prick evenly close together with a fork.
Sugar lightly; bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes until tan, not brown.
Immediately cut into bars after removing from oven.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from water and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook spaghetti noodles in same water, drain and rinse with cold water.
Saute onion in butter.
Place all ingredients in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Place cucumber slices in a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover bowl and chill for one hour; drain.
Mix other ingredients together; stir into cucumber slices.
To serve, sprinkle sliced radishes over the top.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: frozen jello delight
directions: Combine pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Add Eagle Brand milk and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in freezer; will keep indefinitely.

title: onion ring loaf
directions: Slice onions into 1/4-inch rings.
Combine eggs and milk in medium bowl.
Put flour and salt into large bowl.
Heat oil to 385° in deep fryer.
Dip a deep frying basket into hot oil and remove to foil-lined cookie sheet for awhile.

title: rich chocolate pudding(4 servings)
directions: Coarsely chop the chocolate.
Set aside.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together in a small saucepan until blended.
Gradually stir in milk until blended; add chopped chocolate.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until chocolate is melted and mixture begins to boil.
Cook, stirring, until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Pour into 4 custard cups.
Cool at room temperature before serving.
Can be garnished with whip cream or berries of your choice.

title: baked alaska
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch pan. Use rest of batter for cupcakes; cool.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the shortening, sugar, salt and egg, mix well.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Beat after each cup until the mixture pulls away from the sides of bowl and is slightly dry.
Put on a well floured board and knead well. Form into a ball and put in a well greased bowl, grease top of dough and cover well.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
When ready to use, punch down the dough and remove the amount needed, refrigerate any unused amount.
Form into rolls about the size of a walnut.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Allow to rise until double (about 1 hour) in a warm place out of drafts.
Bake at 400 degree oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Dough will keep 1 week.

title: tortilla things
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Refrigerate to harden the cheese a little.
This will make them easier to slice.
Slice and serve.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Cook until done. Stir in milk and cheese; blend well.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: filled eggs
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs into halves.
Remove the egg yolks; mash and blend with cream cheese, soft butter and mustard.
Stir in chopped beets, horseradish and a dash of sugar.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff eggs and decorate with beets.

title: hominy au gratin
directions: Combine hominy, onion and pimento in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour. Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly and thickened. Stir in cheese.
Heat until melted.
Pour over hominy, mixing. Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350° until nice and brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on large cookie sheet and press together to cover pan to make crust.
Spray with Pam first.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10
minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and shredded cheese.

title: lemon pudding roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes;
add sugar gradually until light and fluffy.
Add water & vanilla.
Mix well.
Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Pour into a greased, foil-lined cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Loosen edges and roll into a dish towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box and cool.
Unroll and spread evenly with lemon filling.
Roll up and chill.

title: jellosicles
directions: Mix jello and hot water well. Then add cold water.
Stir and pour into ice cube trays.
Insert popsicle stick in center when slightly frozen.
Freeze.

title: pineapple chiffon cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch Bundt pan.
Sift flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add egg yolks, juice and lemon peel.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until double in volume.
Add remaining sugar gradually and beat until stand in soft peaks.
Add egg yolk mixture and fold in gently.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool on wire racks 10 minutes.
Loosen around edges.
Ease out of pan and continue to cool on wire racks.

title: potato bake
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and add milk slowly.
Add salt and cayenne.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Reduce heat and add cheese.
Add bell pepper and pimento.
Pour sauce over potatoes in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tater-burger bake
directions: Lightly spoon hamburger, seasoned with salt and pepper, into a greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Cover with diced onion.
Top with Tater Tots.
Pour soup over top.
Gently pour hot water over all. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken fried steaks
directions: Combine 1 egg, buttermilk, water and Worcestershire sauce, mixing well. Set aside.

title: 4 x 4 cruiser
directions: Combine all into mixing glass half filled with ice cubes. Stir well and strain into cocktail glass.

title: dip dip hooray
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: stuffed baked apples
directions: Melt apricot preserves; stir in Amaretto.
Add to half of this glaze the almonds and raisins; use as stuffing for apples.
Wrap each filled apple in foil.
Place in pan with small amount of water.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Brush with remaining glaze and return to oven for 5 minutes until apples are golden and gooey.
Accompany with sweet or sour cream.
Serves 8.

title: cassandra's cinnamon biscuits
directions: Place biscuits in greased baking pan.
Heavily sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on biscuits.
Bake at 425° until done. Sprinkle 10x sugar on hot biscuits.
Optional:
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: strawberry-rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Combine pineapple, rhubarb and sugar in saucepan.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Pour into 3 pint jars or plastic containers and freeze.

title: catfish stew
directions: Cut catfish into 1-inch cubes.
Combine fish and onions in a large soup pot.
Add enough water to just cover.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer and cook until fish feathers out (flakes).
In a separate pot, cook potatoes, then add to stew. Add salt, pepper and red peppers to taste.
Add tomato paste and mashed tomatoes.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble into stew.
Let stew cook to desired thickness, then add milk.
Stir well and let simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Make Roux:
Brown 1/2 cup flour in oil (make consistency to be like thick pea soup).
Stir at all times.
Let it get very brown (a red brown).
Take off fire.
Pour in all ingredients.
Add water until thin.
Let cook and come to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for hours.
Serve over rice, plain or sprinkle more file over it.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until well mixed. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: hot herb biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll dough out on a floured surface to desired thickness and cut with a small cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 2 dozen biscuits.

title: peanut butter cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Beat together mashed banana, peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Beat well.
Stir in chopped peanuts.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly oiled cookie sheets.
Press each cookie down with the back of a fork and again in the opposite direction to indent a checkered pattern into each cookie.
(Wet the fork with cold water occasionally to avoid sticking.)
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend Jell-O instant vanilla pudding mix and cold milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip; blend well.
Add vanilla ice cream; mix well.
Add bananas and vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate overnight or prepare early in the morning for evening dessert.

title: peanut butter crisps
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to sugar/butter mixture and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on oiled cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press with back of fork to flatten, making crisscrosses.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, pudding and poppy seed.
Mix together then add boiling water and almond.
Put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: torte
directions: Combine above and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups of boiling water and let cool.
Boil 4 cups sugar and 4 cups of water until dissolved.
Let cool.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in oven in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until light brown.
Cool; chill. Cut into bars.

title: rarebit scramble
directions: In a double boiler, melt butter or margarine.
Add cheese. Stir occasionally until melted.
With a fork, beat until blended the eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Stir into cheese.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until partially thickened and fairly smooth. Serve on toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with 1/2 to 3/4 jar of chunky salsa.
Chop onion and peppers into very small pieces.
In skillet, saute peppers with onion.
Blend into cream cheese mixture.
Add sliced black olives. Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt cream cheese in soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease a mold or Bundt pan with mayo.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix all together.
Add nuts.
Put mixture in two greased loaf pans and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: quick and easy jello pie(steve's and clyde's favorite)
directions: Chill milk ahead of time; whip milk until stiff.
Add in sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve jello in warm water and add to milk. Pour into pie shells.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with whipped or any other fruit topping.

title: lumpia
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add egg, beans, cabbage, bean sprouts, carrots, soy sauce, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: ickey gooey cake
directions: Mix with a fork. Crumble into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni, cheese, and ham casserole(silver bowl winner 1988)
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package. Simmer ham, green peppers, and onion in butter; add salt.
Cook until tender.
Stir in prepared macaroni and cheese dinner.
Add sharp cheese; mix well.
Simmer 10 - 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: *halvah
directions: Combine the water, sugar, cloves, cinnamon stick and lemon peel.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 minute.
Remove cloves, cinnamon stick and lemon peel. Set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, drain and blot spinach dry.
Mix well with other ingredients. Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool and slice.
Combine rest of ingredients; add potatoes.

title: country style corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease skillet and place in oven to heat. Measure meal into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Pour the batter into hot greased pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 5 minutes.
Stuff with remaining ingredients; cover with sauce. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan tassie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and margarine, then add flour. Chill at least 1 hour. Pinch off 1-inch balls (about the size of a quarter) and place in tiny ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cups. Press dough onto bottom and sides of cups. Makes about 3 dozen miniature shells.
